title: breast of chicken "au champignon"
directions: Flatten breasts of chicken slightly. Roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Lightly brown in butter over low heat. Add mushrooms, cover and simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add all-purpose cream and simmer 7 minutes. Transfer chicken to platter.
Add wine to liquid in skillet. Bring to a rapid boil.
Cook until reduced to a creamy consistency.
Pour sauce over chicken. Serve with rice or rice pilaf.

title: dish for large dinner
directions: Simmer on stove all ingredients mixed together about 10 minutes.
In microwave cook about 3 minutes.
In crock-pot cook until heated through.
Recipe can be halved.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Combine.
Make into balls.
Brown in skillet.
Will make 20 to 25 medium size balls.

title: clam puffs
directions: Mix to consistency of hush puppy mix.
Use saved liquid if needed.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil and cook like hush puppies.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry cake with strawberry icing
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, Jello, strawberries and crisco oil together, pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: pork and beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
The
next
morning
add pork and salt. Cook slowly until
nearly
done.
Make
a
sauce
with remaining ingredients.
Fill
cans
full
of beans.
Fill with tomato sauce.
Makes 15 quarts.
Cold pack for 3 hours or process in pressure canner at 10 pounds pressure, quarts for 1 hour and 15 minutes and pints for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: In a blender or food processor, mix onion, garlic and jalapeno pepper well.
Then add remaining ingredients and blend to desired consistency.

title: egg casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown. Blend flour and milk; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Add cheese and stir until melted. Place half the egg slices into bottom of a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 1-inch dish. Cover with half the cheese sauce, half the potato chips and half the crumbled bacon. Repeat layers. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add blueberries and pineapple to Jell-O.
Refrigerate until firm.
Soften cream cheese. Mix soft cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold in sour cream and spread on top of Jell-O mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: crackerjacks
directions: Cook all ingredients, except popcorn and nuts, to hard ball stage.
Mix with popcorn; mix well.
Pour into large baking pan. Bake in 200° oven for one hour.
Stir often.
Let cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: hot sauce dip
directions: Drain tomatoes into blender.
(I also put about 1/3 of the tomatoes in the blender.)
Cut the rest of the tomatoes into small chunks.
Add other ingredients.
Blend for about 5 seconds.
Add to chunked tomatoes.
Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: grace church 12-bean soup
directions: Wash beans and barley.
Place in large kettle; cover with water to 2 inches above beans.
Add the salt (optional).
Soak overnight; drain in the morning.
Add 2 quarts water and ham bone or hock. Bring to boil; simmer slowly for 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Remove ham bone or hock.
Cut off meat; chop and return to soup. Add onion, tomatoes, chili powder, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer slowly 1 or more hours.
Serve with a tossed salad and cornbread or crusty French bread.
Enjoy!!!

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add cream cheese and milk.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve hot.

title: quick and easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.
Add pasta and cook for 8 to 10 minutes, or until al dente; drain and return to pot.
To the pasta add the diced tomatoes with green chili peppers, cream of chicken soup, processed cheese, chopped chicken, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.

title: bull only sandwich
directions: Prepare with care.
Spread mustard on the inside portion of one slice of bread, then spread mayonnaise on the inside portion of the other slice of bread.
Next place the onion slice on the mustard side of first slice of bread, then place bologna (1 slice) over the onion slice.
Now place the slice of cheese over this slice of bologna, then the other slice of bologna over the cheese.
Now you are ready to place the slice of tomato over this second slice of bologna, and the last slice of bread over this.
(Be sure mayonnaise side is next to the tomato.)
Ready to devour.

title: apple-pineapple ham
directions: Place ham in disposable 11 x 9 x 2-inch foil pan and set in supporting pan or roasting pan of equivalent size.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of ham, not touching bone.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: crunchy tuna dip
directions: (I cook onion a little in the microwave first.)
In medium mixing bowl, blend cheese and tuna until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix together 1 package dry yeast and 1/2 cup warm water; set to side.
Beat together the sugar, 1/2 cup hot water, the salad oil and salt.
Cool and stir in the egg and yeast mixture.
Add 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add 1 cup flour with spoon.
Let raise in bowl until twice its size (1 to 2 hours).
Roll into small balls, then put 2 per muffin tin.
Let raise 3 hours, covered. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pink lassies
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; cover and whip until smooth. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: low-fat ham and beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in a large bowl of water.
The next morning, drain and place in a large crock-pot.
Add rest of ingredients and cook on high 5 to 6 hours, until beans are tender.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Cream shortening and extract together.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, beating thoroughly.

Mixing until well blended after each addition, alternately add dry ingredients in fourths and a mixture of evaporated milk and lemon juice in thirds to the creamed mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks are formed; fold into batter. Drop by tablespoon 3-inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove cookies to cooling rack.
Makes around 5 dozen.

title: chicken biscuits
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine.
Add cubed chicken breast, salt, pepper, milk and onion; mix well.
Separate the rolls into 8 rectangles.
Seal the perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners to center; pinch together to seal.
Brush tops with 1/2 teaspoon butter; dip in croutons or cornflakes.
(Can sprinkle this mixture on top, if you like.)
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Shake or roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Put in well-greased Bundt pan.
Melt sugar, brown sugar, margarine and nuts in saucepan.
Mix well.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let cool at least 10 minutes before inverting contents onto plate.
Great recipe to have kids help with.
They love cutting the biscuits and shaking them.

title: pretzel jello dessert
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pretzels and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Press lightly onto bottom of pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: easy pineapple sheet cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour a 9 x 12-inch pan. Beat eggs, then mix together the other 5 ingredients until thoroughly blended. Pour into prepared pan and bake until done, about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry-lemon cheesecake(serves 12 to 16)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine crumbs, sugar, butter and egg white.
Blend.
Press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Place pan on baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until slightly brown.
Cool on rack.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.

title: strawberry banana pie
directions: Slice bananas into the pie crusts (3 or 4 in each).
Beat cream cheese and sugar together until it is creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix well.
Spread this over the bananas.
Prepare strawberries (wash and slice them).
Stir glaze into them gently and place on top of pie.
Refrigerate.

title: jean's egg custard
directions: Beat all ingredients in a large bowl; pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: polish wieners
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and jalapeno peppers.
Simmer ingredients for 20 minutes.
Add wieners and simmer another 10 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: cool whip topping
directions: Mix the milk and pudding (any flavor). Beat together until it has thickened. Then blend in the Cool Whip. Finally, pour on cake.

title: fried rice
directions: In small bowl, beat together egg and egg whites; set aside. Place large nonstick saucepan or wok over medium-high heat 30 seconds. Add oil. Heat 30 seconds; add onions, celery and garlic. Cook, stirring constantly, until soft, about 5 minutes. Reduce heat to low; add eggs. Cook, stirring gently, until set, 1 minute. Stir in peas. Cook, tossing lightly, 2 minutes. Sprinkle with soy sauce and toss lightly. Serve immediately to prevent sogginess.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix using package directions using a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pierce cake with a fork. Mix milk and caramel topping together. Pour over baked cake. Sprinkle with half of candy crumbs. Spread with whipped topping and then rest of candy.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all together very well and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine lemon juice and peel, sugar and butter in saucepan; cook over low heat until butter is melted and sugar is dissolved. Stir a small amount of hot mixture into eggs; return to saucepan. Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened, stirring constantly (do not boil).
Cool thoroughly.

title: nanny marge's date loaf
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, milk, syrup, margarine and dates.
Cook to soft-ball stage (240°).
Add pecans and vanilla.
Beat until mixture becomes firm.
Pour onto damp clean kitchen towel and shape into 1 1/2-inch roll.
Refrigerate until firm.
Slice to serve.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Boil
broken
cobs in the water for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat
and
strain the liquid.
If not 3 cups, add enough water
to make
3 cups.
Add Sure Jell and bring to a rolling boil.
Add sugar and boil 2 or 3 minutes or until jelly stage. The
finished product tastes a lot like apple jelly and has an attractive reddish color.

title: carol's banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour. Line pan with waxed paper.

title: refrigerated mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until light and fluffy.
May be used within 2 weeks.
Place desired amount in greased casserole.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or eat as is.
Good hot or cold.

title: croquettes de poisson
directions: Peel onions and shallots.
Finely chop with mushrooms and parsley or in a food processor until coarse fine.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in pan; add vegetables and cook over low heat until all liquid is gone and vegetables are soft.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of flour and stir well, then pour in the boiling milk, stirring well.
Grind fish fillets.
Add to pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover over low heat for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Break 1 egg into shallow dish and beat.
Put the bread crumbs and remaining flour on 2
plates.
Beat remaining eggs and gradually blend into the fish mixture in a thin stream.
Leave to cool.
Shape fish into walnut size balls and flatten slightly. Dip them in flour, then egg and in bread crumbs.
Drop croquettes few at a time in hot oil and cook 10 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and serve piping hot.

title: bacon-wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Marinate water chestnuts in soy sauce for 30 minutes.
Roll in brown sugar.
Wrap in bacon pieces.
Secure each with a toothpick. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in broiler pan so chestnuts will not sit in grease.
Can be done ahead and reheated for 5 minutes at 350° before serving.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: snicker bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven, using cookie package directions.
Press cookie dough into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake using cookie package directions.
Arrange candy over baked layer.
Bake just until candy is softened; spread evenly over surface.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: carrot bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 375° for 55 minutes.
I use 350°.
You know your oven.
I have used everything in this but carrots.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Press dough evenly into 12-inch pizza pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool and place on serving plate. Spread whipped topping on cookie crust and garnish with fruit. Can serve immediately or refrigerate. Serves approximately 12.

title: frito salad
directions: Combine in large bowl the cut lettuce, tomatoes, onion and cheese.
Drain and rinse beans; add to other ingredients.
Just before serving, add Fritos and Catalina dressing and mix well.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Toast coconut in oven; sprinkle on top. Put red cherry on top.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In large heavy saucepan, dissolve soda in buttermilk over low flame.
Add sugar and Karo syrup and cook stirring over medium heat until soft ball forms when a small amount is dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Beat several minutes with wooden spoon.
When mixture starts to thicken, drop by large spoonfuls onto wax paper to harden.
Store in airtight container.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin tins.
Combine Bisquick and 1/4 cup sugar in bowl.
Make a "well" in center of mixture. Add sour cream and egg.
Beat with a fork until well combined. Fold in blueberries with rubber scraper.
Scoop 1/4 cup batter into each muffin cup (12 muffins).

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple; add jello and stir until well dissolved.
Let cool.
Then add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Stir and mix well.
Pour into bowl and chill.

title: sweet & sour cocktail wieners
directions: Mix mustard and jelly.	Heat in a double boiler.
Slice wieners and add to sauce.

title: old-fashioned orange cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, eggs, oil, orange peel and orange juice. Mix well. Drop mixture by the teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet. If desired, top each cookie with a pecan half.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes or until golden. Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute, then remove to cooling rack to finish cooling.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Follow directions on package for preparing jello with the exception of substituting pineapple juice, drained from crushed pineapple, for the one cup of cold water.
After adding the one cup of hot water to the jello, add cream cheese and stir until it is melted.
Add the pineapple juice, pineapple, nuts and celery. Pour into chilled dish or molds.
Place in refrigerator.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all together; bake in casserole dish for 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: lemon chess cake
directions: Blend butter and 1 egg and mix with cake mix.
Pat into baking dish (15 x 10-inch).

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic in olive oil.
Add to rest of ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour then at 300° for 2 to 3 hours in bean pot.

title: marinated potato and mushroom salad
directions: In a large, shallow dish, combine oil, lemon juice, mustard, sugar and bouillon; mix well.
Add potatoes, mushrooms, celery and onions.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator 3 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: turkish salad
directions: Peel and dice cucumbers into small pieces.
Mix cucumbers and yogurt in serving dish.
Add garlic salt to taste.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Put 1 pie crust in oven and cook around 350° to 375°. You will only want to soften top crust. Do not bake top crust. In bowl, mix chicken, soup and vegetables. Salt and pepper to taste. Pour into baked pie crust. Dot with butter. Cover and seal with other pie crust. Cut a few slits on top. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, until good and brown. Serve with rice.

title: angel macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cover baking sheet with aluminum foil or heavy brown paper.
In large mixer bowl, blend cake mix, soda pop and almond extract on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally 1 minute.
Fold in coconut.
Drop batter by teaspoon about 2 inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake until set for 10 to 12 minutes. Slide foil with cookies onto wire rack.
Cool cookies completely before removing from foil.
Store cookies in freezer or between layers of waxed paper in a box.

title: chocolate gravy or chocolate breakfast syrup
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour, then add water.
You may use milk, if you wish.
Cook over low heat until syrup starts to get thick. Do not overcook. Add vanilla. Serve on hot buttered biscuits.

title: sherry chicken with rice
directions: Rinse chicken breast with cold water and pat dry.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except rice.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve chicken gravy over rice.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: witches stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: lace cookies
directions: Pour margarine over oatmeal in mixing bowl.
Sift dry ingredients and mix with oatmeal.
Beat egg and add.
Add vanilla, blending into mixture.
Add pecans.
Cover cookie sheet with foil and drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 325° for approximately 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool before removing from foil.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Simmer 15 minutes or until slightly thickened.

title: keema curry (ground beef curry)(indian food)
directions: My Mother is horrified at my method, but I don't want to fuss over a lot of frying, so I put all the ingredients and the ground beef into the saucepan and stir the whole concoction together.
I add about 1/2 to 3/4 cup water and then let the curry cook on low heat until the hamburger is done.
I also add fresh cut potatoes, carrots, peas and cauliflower to the curry and presto!
It's all there and done!

title: quicky bean bake
directions: Cook bacon in frying pan; drain most of fat but leave a little to saut onions.
Set cooked bacon on paper towel.
Drain cans of pork and beans; add to sauteed onions and rest of ingredients.
Let simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Then put in crock-pot for 2 hours or more.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Stir and mix the puddings and jello in a bowl.
Use the juice from the fruit; add water to make 3 cups.
Boil juice.
Pour over jello and puddings.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: pretzel crust cherry pie
directions: Mix melted margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Stir in pretzels to coat well.
Pat pretzel mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: cornbread skillet casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl; set aside.
Cook ground beef until browned; drain well and set aside.
Pour half the cornmeal mixture into a greased 10 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet. Sprinkle evenly with beef.
Top with cheese, onion and peppers. Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: health nut sandwich
directions: Spread Dijon mustard on 2 slices of whole wheat bread.
Put a slice of Swiss cheese on each.
Put sliced tomato and sprouts on one piece of bread; put sliced turkey on the other.
Grill together.
A great sandwich and low in calories!

title: mexican soup
directions: Cook the onion in the margarine until soft.
Add corn, zucchini, tomatoes and water to suit you.
Add McKay's to suit your taste.
Heat through.
When hot, add milk to suit your taste. Serve over cubed cheese. Put cubes in the bottom of the soup bowl.
Pour on soup and allow to just melt the cheese.

title: easy christmas punch
directions: Combine equal amounts of punch and ginger ale.
Freeze cherries in water in round jello mold.
Float ice ring in punch for "wreath" look.

title: best ever fried rice
directions: Arrange all ingredients for easy access.
Whisk eggs together in a small bowl.
Preheat wok or skillet on medium to medium-high heat.
Add peanut oil and heat 1 minute.
Then add eggs and let cook for 1 minute, without stirring, or until top is moist and bottom is cooked.
Add rice and toss with eggs, coating rice with moist egg while chopping in cooked egg.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes, then add scallions, carrots and ham.
Stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes more.
Add peas and soy sauce; toss until heated through.
Serves 4.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together the first 3 ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla. Cream together with the shortening, peanut butter and sugars. Roll into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and put a chocolate kiss on each.
Press until cookie cracks.
Bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: finger steaks
directions: Combine milk and egg.
Beat slightly.
Add dry ingredients slowly, mixing each addition very thoroughly to prevent lumps.
Cut steak in 1-inch cubes.
Deep-fry at 325° for 5 minutes until brown.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine juice with ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch and soy sauce; stir to blend. Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken.
Stir-fry 3 minutes. Remove chicken.
Add bell pepper and onion.
Stir-fry 3 minutes. Add water chestnuts and juice mixture.
Cook, stirring until boils and thickens.
Add chicken and pineapple.
Simmer.
Serve over warmed chow mein noodles or steamed rice.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare pudding according to box instructions.
Mix together peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbled.
Press half of the crumbs in bottom of pie shell.
Place cooled vanilla pudding in pie shell.
Put rest of crumbs on top.
Top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, syrup and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into two unbaked pastry shells.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Part 1:
Spread wafer crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup warm water.
Add 2 cups of water, salt, egg, sugar and shortening.
Put flour as needed, about 7 cups.
Spread mixture on floured board.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Place in oiled bowl, turning to oil surface.
Cover with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator until needed.
Shape dough into rolls.
Place on greased baking pan.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 25 minutes. Yield: 24 rolls.

title: salmon soup
directions: Place salmon, butter and salt and pepper on heat until butter melts. Scald 2 cups milk. Add together. A potato cooked with salmon will add thickness. Instant onion will also enhance flavor.

title: old fashion cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk, nutmeg, baking soda and flour.
Stir in milk and vanilla until a stiff dough forms.
Chill 15 minutes, if desired.
Roll out on lightly floured board.
Cut with bottle cap a decorative round.
Just off center with fork, pierce all over.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes or until golden.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, oleo and sugars.
Add beaten eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla, then add flour, salt and soda.
At the last, mix in the oats, nuts and coconut by hand.
Grease cookie sheet. Drop by spoonful and mash down with fork.
You can also make a roll and wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli a few minutes.
Combine margarine, soup (diluted with 1/2 cup milk), Cheez Whiz and about 1 tablespoon chopped onion.
Heat this on stove until cheese is melted.
Layer broccoli and cooked rice in baking dish.
Pour heated mixture over broccoli and rice.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
More chicken the better!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: souper meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup mushroom soup, onion soup mix, beef, crumbs and egg.
In 2-quart, oblong baking dish, firmly shape into an 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done. Spoon off fat; reserve 1 to 2 tablespoons drippings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain well.
Mix ground beef, onion, pepperoni, spaghetti sauce and noodles.
Layer ground beef and Mozzarella cheese in a casserole dish, ending with Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: barbecue burgers(sloppy joes)
directions: Brown meat lightly; add other ingredients and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix eggs, flour, salt, pepper and water.
Soak pork in batter. Deep fry.

title: chicken wings teriyaki
directions: Roll fresh chicken wings in cornstarch and then deep fry until golden brown.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, soy sauce and chives in a bowl.
Add 3 to 4 drops of Tabasco, if desired.

title: tomato bisque
directions: In a deep saucepan, melt butter.
Saute onion and garlic until golden.
Slice tomatoes and add with dry mustard, salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in tomato paste.
(If tomatoes are not full flavored, you may wish to add more paste.) Add flour and chicken broth, then bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Puree in a blender, then strain to remove seeds and skins.
Add 1 to 2 cups light cream.
Reheat to serve, but do not boil.
Add sherry to taste.

title: white bread
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Put in the cold water. Soften yeast in the warm water.
Mix all together then start adding the flour.
I usually add half and stir it in and keep adding flour until it is getting hard to do.
Put on floured board and knead for about five minutes.
If it sticks to board, add more flour.
Put in large greased container and let it rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.

title: smokehouse pickles
directions: You will also need a plastic bucket with lid.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Pour off grease.
Mix all other ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: mostaccioli 'al fredo
directions: Prepare Creamettes mostaccioli according to package directions; drain.
In large pan, heat cream and margarine on low heat.
Do not boil.
Add mostaccioli, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Toss gently to coat.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pineapple, nuts and lemon juice.
Pour into crust and chill for 3 hours (better if overnight).

title: salsa sauce
directions: Combine ingredients, bring to boil for 30 minutes in open kettle.
Simmer 20 minutes. Put in jars and process for 20 minutes in boiling water.

title: fudge cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour; stir with a spoon. Add cocoa, water, margarine, and oil in a sauce pan and bring to a boil; add to flour and sugar mixture and stir. Mix soda with buttermilk and stir into the mixture; add eggs and vanilla. Bake in a 13 x 9 inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes. Leave in pan and let cool before icing.

title: white mountain cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg whites; mix well.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix cool ship, dry jello and cottage cheese until jello is dissolved.
Open and drain Mandarin oranges.
Put mandarin oranges into cool whip.
Fold mixture in gently.
Refrigerated for about 1 hour.

title: perfect divinity
directions: Butter sides of 2-quart saucepan.
In it combine sugar, corn syrup, hot water and salt.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boiling.
Cook to hard ball stage without stirring (strings form from spoon).
Remove from heat. Immediately beat egg whites until stiff. Pour hot syrup slowly over stiffly-beaten egg whites, beating constantly at high speed with electric beater (about 5 minutes).
Add vanilla; continue beating until mixture forms soft peaks and begins to lose its gloss.
Add chopped nuts.
Drop divinity from teaspoon, pushing off with second spoon on cookie sheet covered with waxed paper.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla, and sour cream. Mix well.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt, and baking soda. Add to cream mixture.
Chill.
Scoop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 12-15 minutes.
Frost with canned sour cream frosting.

title: cocoa cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 30 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups (or if you prefer a cake, grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt cake pan).
Beat all ingredients on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, for 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, for 3 minutes.
Pour into muffin cups.
Bake for 20 minutes (40 to 45 minutes for Bundt cake).
Let cool and then ice with Creamy Cocoa Frosting.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add oil, sugar and vanilla; continue beating until mixture is thick. With spoon, stir in zucchini and pineapple. Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, walnuts and currants. Stir gently into zucchini mixture just until blended. Divide equally between 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° about 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes. Turn out on wire racks to cool.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In a bowl, mix potatoes, onions, salt, pepper, cheese, sour cream, 1/2 cup melted butter and soup.
Spoon into prepared pan.

title: carne con calavasa
directions: In a large frying pan, steam chilies, jalapenos and tomatoes. Push to remove air.
Place in a plastic bag to steam. Remove skins.

title: bayou baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon; remove and drain.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Pour beans into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir bacon and onion into beans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Bake 45 minutes.

title: mexican artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown meat and onion in a small amount of fat.
Add tomato soup and beans (I like to mash half of the beans with a potato masher), chili powder, salt, vinegar and enough water for the desired consistency.
Cook about 20 minutes on medium heat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with salt for 30 minutes.
When cooked, tear into pieces and put in bottom of deep casserole dish.
Then spread can of cream of mushroom soup on top of chicken.
Then spread the package of dressing on top of soup.
Sprinkle sage next.
In bowl, mix eggs with 1 can of chicken broth that the chicken cooked in. Use the soup can to measure broth.
Pour this over chicken in casserole dish.
Cut up onion and celery and place on top next. Cut up the margarine and put on top of onion and celery.
Cut bread into squares and place on top.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake approximately 1 hour.

title: rum balls
directions: Melt chocolate over hot (not boiling) water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Let ripen in tight container for at least 1 week.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all except noodles.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Serve.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a long pan and place cabbage slices over bottom.
Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch round slices. Place over cabbage and carrots.
Slice onion in thick slices and place over potatoes.
Cut sausage roll into 1/4-inch slices and place on onions.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and add milk for desired spreading consistency.

title: dixie relish
directions: Soak peppers 24 hours in 1 cup salt and 1 gallon of water. Freshen in fresh water for 1 or 2 hours.
Drain and chop each separate (then measure).
Mix all together.
Add seasonings and let stand in a crock overnight.
Drain off vinegar.
Remove bubbles, seal and process.

title: hickory stick salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add enough water to equal 2 cups.
Heat liquid; pour over jello.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl; pour jello over and mix well.
Mold in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sarah's yams
directions: Peel and cut yams into 1-inch cubes.
Steam yams until soft. Beat yams with mixer beater until smooth.
Add margarine and milk. Serve as an accompaniment to ham or pork.

title: pumpkin chip cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for approximately 14 minutes.

title: mexican chicken(serves 6)
directions: Boil chicken and debone, tear into small pieces.
Combine in pan and heat on low the cream of chicken, cream of mushroom, Cheddar cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Dip tortillas in soup sauce and layer in dish.
Sprinkle on layer of onion, chicken and chilies.
Spoon some sauce on top.
Repeat layering until everything is used up.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and melted.
To make it hotter, use some jalapeno peppers.

title: pecan chewys
directions: Blend together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with a wire whisk and blend in sweetened condensed milk.
Add grated lime rind and lime juice; mix well. Pour into crust.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: vegetable biriani
directions: Wash and soak the rice for 10 minutes.
Deep fry the Ricotta cheese in butter and keep aside.
Fry the onion and bay leaf in butter until brown; add chili powder, salt, cloves, cardamom, cinnamon, cumin seed, powder and water and boil.
Add carrot slices, rice, peas and fried Ricotta cheese and cook until the rice has absorbed all the water and each grain is separate.
Fry the potatoes and add it to the dish and cover the vessel.
At the end, add the coriander to garnish.
Serves 6.

title: vegetarian milkshake
directions: Into a blender, pour a little apple juice, a small handful of cashew nuts, a little honey, half a banana, a dash of pure vanilla and nonfat dry milk or soy milk.
At this point you can add berries, peanut butter, carob powder or any flavor you desire. Then add handfuls of crushed ice and continue blending until the shake is thick and smooth.

title: sweet and sour burger loaf
directions: Melt margarine and saute chopped onion and bread cubes. Combine onions and bread cubes with burger, cheese, eggs and spices.
Press into oiled 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, carrots and onion (I use a food processor). Mix water, sugar and vinegar; pour on veggies and let sit a few hours.
Drain off liquid.
Mix with mayo.
Season to taste with salt.

title: caramel rolls
directions: For 1 loaf, use 10 x 7-inch pan.
For 2 loaves, double recipe and use one 9 x 13-inch and one 10 x 7-inch pan.

title: hasty pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk.
Beat for 1 to 2 minutes until well blended.
Stir in rice and raisins.
Spoon pudding into individual bowls.
Chill.
Garnish with whipped topping and a cherry.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Chop onion and cut grapes in half.
Add sunflower seeds.
Crumble cooked bacon and mix together.
Then mix mayonnaise, sugar and red wine vinegar, pour over salad mixture and chill in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Mix well.
Beat egg yolks.
Add.
Cook until thick.
Add butter. Swirl on meringue.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: easy 1-2 lemonade dessert
directions: In large bowl, mix together the 2 ingredients until soft. Pour into 2 deep graham cracker crumb crusts.
Cover with foil and freeze.
Easy and quick on a hot, summer day.
You may make your own crust with graham crackers and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
You may add yellow food coloring too, but not necessary.

title: 1-2-3 cake
directions: Cream together margarine (melted and sugar.
Add eggs.
Pour flour in a little at a time while mixing.
Add milk.
Pour into layer pans and bake at 325° until brown.
Makes 4 layers.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix vinegar, mustard, sugar and salt to Miracle Whip.
Let stand 10 to 20 minutes to thicken.
Pour over warm cooked macaroni.
Add eggs, onion and celery seed.
Mix well, then refrigerate.

title: two-tone brownies
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar.
Melt shortening over boiling water; add to sugar mixture.
Add flour and mix until smooth.
Spoon 1/4 of the batter into a small bowl.
To the remaining batter, add chocolate and pecans.
Spread in a well-greased pan.
To the 1/4 batter, add coconut and spread over chocolate batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese twists
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, mustard, salt and red pepper in large bowl. Reserve 1 Tbsp. cheese; stir remaining cheese into flour mixture. Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Add egg yolks and water, mixing until dough forms. Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm. Preheat oven to 400°. Grease two cookie sheets. Roll out dough on lightly floured surface into 12 inch square (about 1/8 inch thick). Brush surface lightly with egg white and sprinkle with remaining 1 Tbsp. cheese and sesame seeds, if desired. Cut dough in half. Cut each half crosswise into 1/4 inch strips. Twist 2 strips together. Repeat with remaining strips. Place 1 inch apart on prepared cookie sheets. Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from cookie sheets and cool completely on wire racks. Store in airtight container. Makes about 48 twists.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread
directions: Mix soda in boiling water; stir well.
When it stops foaming, add syrup and set aside.
Sift dry ingredients, except sugar.
Set aside.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Spray 10-inch square Corning Ware dish with Pam.
Lay artichoke hearts on bottom.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour on top.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Stir the top a little and microwave for 10 more minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and stir.
Place small amount on bottom of pan.
Lay 3 to 4 (depending on size of pan) lasagna noodles on top of sauce. Spread small amount of cottage cheese over noodles.
Then add Mozzarella, yellow and Parmesan cheeses.
(Government surplus cheese can be used for yellow cheese.)
Pour about 1/2 of the remaining sauce over this.
Lay the other noodles on top of this, then cottage cheese, but this time, put less of the other cheese. Pour on rest of sauce and rest of cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° (until noodles test fork-tender).

title: microwave chinese chicken
directions: Mix oil with soy sauce, ginger and garlic powder.
Place chicken in glass baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover loosely with wax paper.
Cook on High 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Rotate baking dish halfway through cooking time.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter roll ups(childrens recipe)
directions: Flatten bread with rolling pin.
Spread with peanut butter and roll up.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, chiles, sour cream and picante sauce.
Add half of the mixture to precooked chicken.
Warm tortillas and fill with chicken mixture and half of grated cheese.
Roll up.
Place in greased casserole.
Cover with remaining half of cream mixture and other half of cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: oven pan fried potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well and cut into wedges.
Mix oil, salt and paprika in bowl.
Add potatoes and toss until coated.
Place potatoes on a foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes; turn once after 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Strawberries, blackberries or raspberries may be substituted.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Saute cabbage, onion and garlic in oil.
Add soy sauce.
Put in baking dish.
Combine milk and egg and pour over cabbage.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Don't overbake.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat cookie dough in a cake pan or a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch carefully!
Let cookie dough cool.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together and press into a loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: potato latkes
directions: Break one egg into blender. Add 2 1/2 potatoes, 1/2 onion and 1/2 carrot in blender. Put blender on grate. Pour mixture into a bowl.
Repeat with remaining 1 egg, 2 1/2 potatoes, 1/2 onion and 1/2 carrot.
Grate in blender. Pour into bowl. Add in matzah meal. Sprinkle in garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly. Heat oil in frying pan.
When hot, drop in tablespoons of latke mix. Fry on both sides until golden brown. Put them on paper towels to absorb the extra oil. Enjoy the delicious snack.

title: fresh cranberry sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine the water and sugar, stirring to dissolve the sugar.
Bring to a boil, and add the cranberries, then reduce the heat to medium-low.
Cook until the skins pop.
Cool the sauce completely at room temperature.
Then refrigerate until firm. Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: chili cornbread
directions: Brown meat and onion in melted shortening.
Add seasoning, Worcestershire sauce and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes; add chili beans.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with cornbread batter and bake for 20 minutes at 250°.
Serves 6.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs with 1 tablespoon water.
Cream thoroughly with sugar and flour.
Add other tablespoon water and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into pie shell.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows, butter and condensed milk in top of double boiler.
Mix in other ingredients.
Pour into boxes lined only with wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Cut chocolate into approximately 1/4-inch chunks.
Combine the flour, salt and cinnamon.
Beat together the butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in the egg.
Stir in the flour mixture.
Add oats, dates and chocolate.
Drop by level teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until the edges brown, 6 to 8 minutes.
Let cool 1 minute before removing to rack.
Bake at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Combine hamburger and onion soup mix.
Spread meat in bottom of baking pan.
Scatter all vegetables over meat mixture.
Spread soup over vegetables.
Spread your Tater Tots over top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Good for covered dish church supper or family affair.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix last three ingredients and let set overnight.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Combine soft margarine, egg, milk, Sugar Twin and vanilla. Blend well.
Mix the dry ingredients and add to mix.
Add applesauce, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon.
Makes 30 cookies, each containing 49 calories.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: orange walnut-date bars
directions: Sift together in a bowl and reserve, flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat butter and sugar until mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, orange rind and juice.
Stir in flour mixture, blending until smooth.
Fold in dates and nuts. Spread evenly in a greased and floured baking tin, 11 x 7 x 1-inch.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned. Spread with Orange Butter Frosting.

title: luscious lemon cheese cake
directions: Prepare a graham cracker crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Put on top of crust.
May cover with Cool Whip.

title: spice cake
directions: Combine salad dressing and sugar.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, spices and salt together.
Add alternately with combined water and molasses.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: date nut bread
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine nuts, dates, soda and salt. Add shortening and water.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix with date/nut mixture.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan prepared with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry apple salad mold
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water. Combine sugar and water.
Bring to a
boil.
Add cranberries and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in softened gelatin until dissolved. Cool and add apples, nuts and celery.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold. Chill until firm.

title: hot banana peppers
directions: Bring to boil.
Wash quart jars; boil lids and rings. Cut hot banana peppers in half; remove seeds and wash.
In clean hot quart jars, pack peppers, fresh dill, a couple cloves of garlic and 1/2 teaspoon alum.
Pour hot liquid in jars.
Wipe tops of jars and seal with hot lids.
The peppers are tangy, but not real hot. Great with a sandwich.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes.
Add instant coffee slowly, stirring, then add vodka or bourbon.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Now enjoy.

title: cappuccino thins(food processor recipe)
directions: In food processor, use regular work blade to chop chocolate using on/off turns until chocolate resembles coarse meal. Transfer to bowl and set aside.
In food processor, combine sugars, egg yolk, coffee, cocoa, cinnamon and salt; mix about 1 minute.
Add butter and mix.
Add flours and chocolate; mix using on/off turns just until flour is incorporated into dough.
Do not over process.
Divide into 4 equal portions.
Form dough into "logs" and wrap each in wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm (about 1 hour) or freeze.
Cut into 1/4 inch slices and put 1 1/2 inches apart on sheet; bake about 8 minutes in 325° oven until set. Transfer to wire rack to cool.

title: steve's "hot" peppers
directions: Combine peppers and oil in frying pan.
Heat to medium.
Chop garlic and add. Flip peppers and rotate until all peppers are completely soft (cooked) all the way through.
Sprinkle with garlic powder as you rotate peppers. Remove cooked peppers.
Put in bowl.
Drain 90% of oil and pour remaining oil and garlic on top of peppers.
Slice peppers and serve on crackers with cheese. Spread garlic oil on bread and serve.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix Wesson oil, margarine and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add these to the oil and sugar mixture.
Add flavoring.
This will be a thick mixture.
Fold in apples, chopped fine (Winesap are better).
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: cheesy crab feast
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Place cream cheese on serving platter.
Press to flatten cheese.
Put crabmeat on top of cheese, then pour cocktail sauce on crabmeat.
Serve with your favorite crackers. This should be prepared right before serving.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix the sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice until thick. Fold in whipped topping which has been partially thawed.
Spoon into the graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight before serving.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread mix and bake per package instructions.
Cool and crumble.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Taste improves if chilled overnight.

title: heavenly angel pie
directions: Mix flour, margarine, sugar and pecans well.
Pat into oblong cake pan and bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Place sliced bananas on top of this.
Prepare pudding according to directions.
Pour on top of bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chile cheese log
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients.
Shape into desired look.
Top with chopped nuts and cheese.

title: lazy day lasagne casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients until blended and set aside.
In medium bowl, mix together sauce and cooked ground beef.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: On low heat, warm milk, shortening and sugar.
Mix in egg, salt and flour.
Mix well in large bowl.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Work down with wood spoon.
Let rise 15 minutes more.
Shape into rolls and place in a greased pan or muffin tin.
Let rise 15 minutes. Bake in hot 400° oven for 15 minutes or until done.

title: chang-chang chicken
directions: Slice chicken or beef in thin strips.
Slice any combination of the vegetables listed in strips or slices for stir-frying.
In a hot skillet, brown chicken or beef in 1 tablespoon of oil. Remove from pan and set aside.
Add remaining oil to skillet. Add desired vegetables, adding mushrooms last.
Cook vegetables until still crunchy as they will continue to cook when sauce is added.
Add chicken or beef back to skillet with the vegetables. Combine sauce ingredients and pour over all.
Cook quickly, then serve over rice.

title: fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar and cook to a rolling boil.
Boil about 10 minutes.
Test mixture to see if it forms a food soft ball when dropped in cold water.
If it does not, cook until it does, stirring constantly.
In a big bowl, combine chocolate chips, marshmallows and butter.
Pour on hot milk and sugar mixture.
Stir until melted.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and pour in large pans and cool.
Makes 6 pounds.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fresh vegetables as an appetizer.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients in large nonmetallic bowl and chill overnight.
Serve soup cold with dollop of sour cream on top of each service.
Pass croutons.
Serves approximately 6 to 8.

title: lucy's creamy fruit dip #1
directions: Soften topping at room temperature. Using an electric mixer, whip together Cool Whip, sour cream, sugar, vanilla and coconut. Chill.
Serve as a dip for fresh fruit or spoon over fresh fruit as a dressing.

title: rotel spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo until done. Add last 3 ingredients. Cook until blended.
Put spaghetti and chicken in a large casserole dish.
Pour the other ingredients over the spaghetti and chicken; mix well. Bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into walnut size balls; bake at 375°.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Combine flour,	salt,
pepper and paprika in paper bag. Drop beef, a
portion at a time; shake until coated.
Mix with Wesson oil in 3 quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Stir
once.
Add	vegetables,
water
and
Hunt's sauce; stir well.	Cover
and
bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jansen farm chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops.
Pour off fat.
Mix together soup and water.
Pour over chops.
Cover; cook over very low heat 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir now and then.

title: peach dream
directions: Set Cool Whip and cream cheese out at room temperature until soft.
Dice canned peaches and save the syrup from the can.
Make jello with 2 cups hot water and 1 cup total of the syrup and cold water.
Let jello begin to set.
Blend cream cheese and Cool Whip in a mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/2 set jello and fold in diced peaches.
Pour into serving dish and chill.

title: holiday salad or dessert
directions: Important, use only glass or plastic bowls for mixing ingredients.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Mix the flour, brown sugar, butter and nuts.
Brown on cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Make topping mix.
Add cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Prepare Danish dessert.
Add frozen berries.
Divide first mixture.
Put 1/2 in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cream cheese mixture; sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Top with berries.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots for a few minutes until partially cooked. Combine all ingredients and bring to a full boil.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until carrots are glazed.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies until mixture resembles dirt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar. In another bowl, mix pudding with milk, 1 to 2 minutes until well blended.
Fold pudding into cream cheese mixture with spatula. Fold in whipped topping.
In an 8 to 10 inch flower pot, or individual pots, alternate cookie crumbs and pudding, ending with cookies.
Place gummy worms into top layer.
Some can be pushed tenderly into the dirt, appearing to be climbing out of the dirt. Chill several hours or overnight.

title: tomato bisque
directions: Cut celery into thirds or just enough to fit into medium size saucepan.
Put all ingredients (except for half and half) into saucepan; bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and let simmer for 20 minutes.
Place mixture in a blender and puree.
Pour into saucepan with half and half and heat through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: purple jello salad
directions: Grind cranberries and whole orange.
Add sugar and set aside. Heat pineapple and juice to boiling; add dry jello, stir until dissolved.
Cool a little and add cream cheese.
Stir until it melts.
Add cranberry mixture, celery, nuts and Cool Whip.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill well.

title: triple treat cookies
directions: Beat shortening until light. Add sugar and continually beat until fluffy.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.

title: rosy glow warm cranberry punch
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot in mugs with orange slices on top or with cinnamon stick stirrers.
Serves 14.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients, then add eggs.
Beat until smooth. Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap bacon around chestnut; slice bacon to fit.
Attach with toothpick.
Pour sauce over them and bake until bacon is done at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican seasoning
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and store in a tightly covered shaker container. Use on meat, poultry, fish and vegetables. Makes 1 cup.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Put all ingredients in big pot and cook. I cook the beef for 1 hour and then add the other ingredients and cook for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown hamburger. In the same skillet add seasoning pack from stuffing mix and water according to package directions. Simmer 2 minutes. Add bread crumbs and let stand. In a separate kettle, bring water to a boil. Add 4-6 green pepper halves. Cook peppers until tender crisp. Stuff peppers with hamburger mixture, alternating with cheese. Put peppers on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350 for 15 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.

title: turkey chowder(low-fat soup)
directions: Heat oil in a large pot.
Saute onion and peppers until onion is translucent.
Add carrots, potatoes, celery, salt and spices. Mix well.
Add stock and simmer for 15 minutes until potatoes and carrots are soft.
Add turkey, corn and pimento.
Heat through but do not boil.
Just before serving, stir in parsley and adjust seasonings to taste.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla wafers which have been crushed, alternately with milk.
Add coconut and pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: light and fruity salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill for at least two hours before serving.

title: lemon curd
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in the top of a double boiler. Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook until butter melts.
Stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into beaten eggs.
Add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium-low heat, until mixture thickens and coats a spoon (about 15 minutes).
Cover and refrigerate up to 2 weeks. Serve over pound cake, angel food cake or gingerbread.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mix together (I put in food processor) and top with lettuce, tomatoes, scallions, black olives and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Combine tomatoes, peppers, onion and salt. Mix well. Let stand 1 hour. Drain well in colander. Put in pan. Add sugar, vinegar and spices. Bring to boil. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes. Put into hot jars and seal. Turn upside down until cool. Good on beans or hot dogs.

title: pie crust - failproof
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening.
Measure 1 egg yolk and milk to equal 2/3 cup.
Reserve egg white.
Beat with 1 teaspoon water and use as glaze on top crust of pie.
Add egg yolk-milk mixture to flour mixture and combine thoroughly.
Roll crust on flour or cloth in usual manner.
Any crust is usually easier to work with if left to set for a few minutes before rolling or put into refrigerator for a few minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream oleo, both sugars and eggs.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well, then stir in oats, chocolate chips and vanilla.
May bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 8 to 10 minutes for cookies.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Break spaghetti into thirds and cook as directed on package. Drain and while still warm, combine with eggs and Parmesan.
Put into 9 or 10-inch pie plate that is well-greased.
Pat up the sides.
Melt butter and saute onions until soft.
Stir sour cream into onions.
Spread over the spaghetti.
Take sausage out of casing and crumble and cook it.
Add sausage to the spaghetti sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon over spaghetti.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Put grated or sliced Mozzarella cheese on top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onion and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and vegetables; reserve.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; let set.
Blend together the milk, vanilla and margarine; combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Beat the egg whites.
Add sugar and vanilla to make meringue. Cover the pie with meringue and brown under broiler. Cool and chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: peas continental
directions: In hot butter in skillet, saute mushrooms and onion about 5 minutes or until tender.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg, marjoram and then peas.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no-fail pound cake
directions: Cream in mixer, sugar and butter slowly until mixed; beat at high speed 4 to 5 minutes.
Add eggs and beat well. Add salt, flour and lemon flavoring. Beat until well mixed, beat at high speed for 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in cold oven.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325° or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin cheesecake(good without graham cracker crust, too)
directions: In a blender, sprinkle gelatin over cold milk; let stand 3 to 4 minutes.
Add hot milk; cover and process at stir (low) for 2 minutes.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Process at liquify (high). With blender running, add cubes of cream cheese one at a time. Reserve 1 cup mixture.
Add pumpkin and pumpkin pie spice in blender; process on high until completely blended.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Swirl in reserved cheese mixture and chill until firm.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all spices together and put in cheesecloth.
Mix apple cider or juice and pineapple juice together.
Pour into large pot and simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: cucumber and tomato salad
directions: Combine water, vinegar, oil and sugar.
Pour over sliced cucumber, tomatoes and onion.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in; chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip tops in sugar.
Sprinkle each with 2 to 3 drops of water.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375° until set but not hard.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Beat together eggs, milk and mustard.
Add sausage, bread, salt and pepper.
Stir to blend.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until lightly browned.
Can be mixed the night before.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken legs until cooked (reserve chicken stock).
Mix chicken meat (skinned and boned), stewed tomatoes, Ro-Tel tomatoes, pimentos, mushrooms and 1 pound of Cheddar cheese. Season with salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Add cooked spaghetti.
Mix well.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream together peanut butter, margarine, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in 3/4 cup of chips.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with remaining chips.
Let stand 5 minutes and spread melted chocolate.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.

title: polynesian dinner
directions: Cook
chickens with ingredients mentioned (covered with water) until
tender.
Cool
and	debone keeping liquid.	Add chicken, one
can
of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup stuffed olives to broth; cook all together and thicken. Place ingredients in row; take some of each things and place on top of each other. Serves 12.

title: salmon ring(microwave)
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Move mixture away from center and place glass in center to make the ring shape.
Cook, uncovered, 8 minutes or until mixture around glass is set.
Remove glass and invert onto a serving plate.
Makes 4 servings.

title: velvet salad
directions: Mix sour cream, Cool Whip and Jell-O; add pineapple and nuts. Chill.

title: master mix
directions: Stir baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and powdered milk into the unsifted flour; sift it all together.
Cut shortening into mixture until it looks like corn meal.
Place in tightly covered container and store at room temperature.
This will keep for months.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add flour and sugar mixed together. Add milk and beat.
Add corn and melted butter.
Cook in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Do not stir.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes until tender.
Mash and add rest of ingredients.
Pour in 3-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Add marshmallows for the last few minutes of baking time.

title: strawberry bavarian pie
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add sugar.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add strawberries.
Fold in whipped topping.
Put in baked pie shell.
You may wish to garnish with a few strawberries. Chill until firm.

title: meat-potato quiche
directions: Baking Temperature: 425°.
Baking Time: 45 minutes, divided.

title: okra
directions: Rinse fresh okra.
Slice lengthwise in half, salt liberally and saute in skillet in olive oil.
Cover and stir occasionally to prevent scorching.
Cook over low-medium heat until okra is very tender.
May add sliced onion, fresh tomato wedges, also bacon or thin pieces of ham at beginning of saute.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add oleo and egg yolks; beat well and add buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into sugar and egg mixture.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie shells. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hershey's cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. To make hot chocolate, use 1/3 cup mix to 2/3 cup hot water.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Mix together and shape into patties.
Fry quickly on both sides.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with 1 can golden mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk or water (mixed together).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: danish sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Cut in butter and shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Blend egg and vanilla; add to dry ingredients.
Mix only until blended. Dough is fairly soft.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in white sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness with bottom of glass dipped in white sugar. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until delicately browned. Makes about 6 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: spoon bread tamale bake
directions: Brown chuck in skillet with oil.
Add onions, garlic, green peppers.
Cook, stirring until onions are golden. Stir in tomatoes, corn, 1 tablespoon salt, chili powder, and black pepper. Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup corn meal mixed with water. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add olives.
Turn into 3 quart casserole dish.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix ingredients together until smooth.
Spread on cake. Garnish with chopped pecans or carrot curls (optional).

title: oven fried okra
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper and set aside.
Wash okra and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Okra must be moist for cornmeal to coat well.
Spray cookie sheet with vegetable cooking spray.
Spread okra in single layer.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until crisp, stirring occasionally. Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll in nuts.
For added "zip" add a few drops of Tabasco.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients all together real good. Drop by teaspoonful on baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: peach pudding
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat egg and pour into margarine and mix. Add sugar, peaches and Cool Whip.
Mix all together.
Layer vanilla wafers and mixture in bowl.

title: honey apple cake
directions: Cream eggs, oil, sugar and honey.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix well.
Then add vanilla, chopped nuts and apples.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until pick placed in center comes out clean.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Squeeze liquid from sauerkraut.
Set aside to drain while preparing the onion, celery and green pepper.
Mix all together. Add sugar, oil and vinegar.
Let mellow for several hours or overnight.

title: mary's brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla; beat in eggs.
Blend in chocolate. Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and ice with frosting. Cut in 16 squares.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and ham biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine the broccoli, ham, cheese, salt and pepper. In another bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add cold butter, cut into bits, and blend until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Stir in buttermilk and form dough into a ball.
Roll the dough into a 16 x 6-inch rectangle on a floured sheet of wax paper; brush with 2 tablespoons melted butter and spread the broccoli mixture evenly over the dough, leaving a 1/2-inch border.

Beginning with a long side, roll up the dough tightly, lifting it with the wax paper and ending seam side down. Cut the dough crosswise into 1-inch slices; put the slices with a cut side down in well buttered muffin tins.
Brush lightly with melted butter.
Bake in the upper third of a preheated 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until they are golden.
Let the buns stand in the tins for 1 minute; loosen the edges with a spatula and serve.
Makes 16 biscuits.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid. Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours, until slightly thickened (consistency of egg whites).
Stir in topping with wire whisk until smooth. Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Stir in pineapple, orange, marshmallows and coconut.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hamburger-tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place hamburger and onion in a large skillet.
Stir hamburger with fork to break up large pieces.
Cook over medium heat until hamburger is browned; drain.
Place hamburger mixture in baking dish.
Add Tater Tots; mix well. Combine soup and milk in mixing bowl; stir well.
Pour soup mixture over hamburger mixture; stir well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas toffee
directions: Take butter, syrup, water and sugar and bring to a boil. Stir continuously about 10 to 12 minutes. Once mixture starts changing colors, add in almonds. When mixture is one shade darker than light brown sugar, pour out onto NONSTICK cookie sheet. Spread with wooden spoon or spatula. Let sit 1 minute and sprinkle chocolate chips over toffee. Chocolate chips will melt and then spread over the toffee, like frosting on a cake. Let toffee completely cool on cookie sheet (couple of hours). Toffee is cool after chocolate is solid on top. Break into bite size pieces and put into airtight container. Great with vanilla bean ice cream.

title: fast 'n fabulous fudge
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine butter or margarine, evaporated milk, sugar and corn syrup.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a full, rolling boil.
Stirring constantly, cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Break chocolate squares into halves; add with marshmallows, chopped walnuts and vanilla to saucepan.
Stir vigorously 1 minute or until chocolate and marshmallows are melted.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Decorate with walnut halves or coconut. Chill in refrigerator until firm, about 1 hour.
Cut into squares. Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: john's meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients with enough bread crumbs to make firm.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cowboy food
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and garlic.
Chop fresh tomatoes in meat and cook until soft.
Add Ranch Style beans and enough water to keep it from sticking.
Add salt and pepper. Simmer about 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: aunt lizzie's date nut cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients and cool.
Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Add vanilla.
Add date mixture, then add flour, salt and nutmeats.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick. Should come out clean.
Bake longer, if necessary.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour
with
1/2 cup sugar.
In large mixing bowl, combine and
beat
until
forms stiff peak:
egg whites, salt, cream of tartar
and
vanilla.
Next
gradually add 1 1/3 cups sugar while
beating
into	mixture.
Fold	in flour and sugar combination.
Fold; do
not
stir.	Pour in tube pan.
Bake in 375° oven
for
45	minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes upside-down. Loosen cake with knife and turn on wire rack to cool.

title: church punch
directions: Mix and add ice ring or cubes.
This makes a large punch bowl.

title: dilled cheese squares
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl pour into ungreased 8 inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees until puffed and lightly browned about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool several minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: fruit cookie pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat together butter and sugars until light and creamy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually blend into butter mixture until just moistened.
Press dough evenly into 12-inch pizza pan or pie crust.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove and cool. Spread with pudding, leaving 1-inch all around.
Arrange fruit on pudding.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough evenly on pizza pan.
(You may also use homemade cookie dough.)
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: banana split cake
directions: Put crust into pan.
Cream the cheese, butter, vanilla and sugar.
Pat into pan slice bananas on top of the cheese mixture. Then pour well drained pineapple on.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts or more graham crackers.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix.
Add Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 2 x 13-inch pan or baking dish, line bottom with whole graham crackers.
Top with layer of pudding mixture.
Alternate layers of graham crackers and pudding mixture.
Top layer will be graham crackers.
Smooth chocolate frosting over top layer of graham crackers and refrigerate for at least 24 hours before serving. Keep refrigerated.

title: hot cheese ball
directions: Shred American and cheddar cheese together. Soften cream cheese with mayonnaise. Combine cheeses and remaining ingredients. Let sit for 1 hour; taste to see if seasoned enough, then shape into balls. Wrap in wax paper then foil. Refrigerate or freeze, soften before serving.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Steam squash and onion for about 5 minutes.
Combine soup (undiluted) and sour cream.
To the soup, add carrots, squash and onion.
In a separate bowl, combine margarine and stuffing mix; spread half of the stuffing mix in a greased 8 x 12-inch pan. Next, spoon the vegetable and soup mixture on top.
Cover with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly and heated through.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, melt margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended.
Continue cooking 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Set aside.
Peel potatoes and slice thin.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: company cauliflower
directions: Separate cauliflower into medium pieces; cook, covered in boiling water, until tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Drain.
Saute green pepper and pimento in margarine; blend in flour.
Gradually stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thick; add salt, mushroom soup and cheese.
Continue stirring until smooth.
Add cauliflower and mix gently until cauliflower is coated.
Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: beer and cheese soup
directions: The sweet onions, leeks, carrots, celery, green and red bell peppers should be finely chopped. Using an 8-quart stockpot, saute the onions, leeks, carrots, celery, green and red pepper in the butter and olive oil until vegetables are softened. Gradually mix in enough of the flour to absorb the buttery oil. Pour in chicken broth and bring to a boil over moderate heat, whisking constantly until the soup thickens slightly. Add the mustard, Worcestershire, Tabasco and mushrooms. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, partially covered, for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Whisk in the cheese, a handful at a time, until it dissolves.
Add the cream, ale (or a wheat beer) and Old Bay seasoning. Bring almost to a boil and serve (DO NOT BOIL).

title: shrimp and cheese appetizer
directions: Wash shrimp, put in bowl - sprinkle with salt, cayenne pepper and squeeze lime over.
Cut and butter bread rounds.
(I use top of sherry glass to cut the bread) Grate cheese, add onion and green pepper.
Drain shrimp and cut small or rub over grater.
Mix all together with a little mayo and spoon onto rounds.
Can be frozen on cookie sheet and put in plastic bag.
Do not thaw.
Put on cookie sheet for 2-3 minutes under broiler until they start to brown, remove and serve immediately.

title: pat ackerman's date-nut bread
directions: Cook dates, covered with water, until partially soft, about 15 minutes.
Drain, saving 1 1/2 cups of the boiling water for the mixture.
Mix all together first 5 ingredients; then add flour and water alternately.
Then stir in baking soda dissolved in water. Lastly add dates and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.
(Line bottom of greased pans with waxed paper.)
Makes 2 loaves.
Use a whisk to mix.

title: avocado stuffed crab salad
directions: Shred crab flakes.
Combine with mayonnaise, celery and onion. Spoon into avocado half that has been brushed with lemon juice. Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: candied grapefruit peels
directions: Score grapefruit into quarters and remove peel.
Place peels in large pan and cover with cold water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes.
Remove peel and allow to cool.
Scrap as much of pith as possible with a spoon.
Cut cleaned peel into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Combine granulated sugar, water and corn syrup in 2-quart pan and bring to boil.
Add peels.
Reduce heat and cook slowly until peels are translucent, about 1 hour.
Set cake rack over baking sheet and remove peels, few at a time, to rack.
Spread out and let excess syrup drip off, about 1 minute.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Clean vegetables.
Break cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Chop green onion (including green stems).
Add crumbled bacon and Cheddar cheese.
Mix separately the Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar.
Add mixture to vegetables; mix thoroughly.
Chill and serve.

title: bacon stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and set whites aside. Place yolks in a bowl and mash and cream.
Add crumbled, crisp bacon, mayonnaise, margarine, mustard and paprika until blended. Spoon mixture into whites.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour or up to 24 hours.

title: pecan cheesecake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract and 1 large egg until smooth. Pour mixture into unbaked pastry crust.
Sprinkle with 1 1/4 cups chopped pecans.

title: linda g's goulash
directions: Boil macaroni for 10 minutes.
At same time, brown ground beef and drain.
Add all other ingredients to beef.
Pour over the macaroni, then sprinkle on the grated cheese.
Serve hot.
May be served with a glass of red wine.

title: batter-fried vegetables
directions: In bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients.
Stir in water and egg until smooth.
Pour oil into large skillet to depth of 1/2-inch.
