Heat over medium heat.
Dip vegetables into batter. Carefully add vegetables to hot oil, a few pieces at a time.
Fry, turning once, two or three minutes or until golden brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool cake and frost.

title: chocolate shake(serves 2)
directions: Dissolve chocolate drink in water to form a paste.
Place in blender with remaining ingredients and blend on medium speed.
Add more water if you prefer a thinner shake.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Squeeze orange.
Pour juice in measuring cup and fill with boiling water to 1 cup level.
Force rind and raisins through chopper.
Add diluted orange juice.
Stir extract, shortening and egg.
Add dry ingredients and beat.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for one hour in a moderate oven.

title: angel biscuits
directions: *For plain flour, add 3 teaspoons baking powder and 1 teaspoon salt.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Grease a pie plate.
Cook beef and onion until brown and drain. Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in plate and top with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand mixer).
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Top with tomato and cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomato, shredded lettuce and shredded cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: huckleberry-lemon custard
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and salt.
Pour into top of double boiler over gently boiling water.
Stir in milk and lemon juice; cook, stirring often, until thickened.
Add lemon peel.
Chill custard. Layer huckleberries and custard in parfait glasses and chill until ready to serve.
Serves 8.

title: m&m's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Set aside. In a large bowl, cream 3/4 cup butter and sugars until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs and vanilla. In medium bowl, combine 2 1/4 cups flour, baking powder and salt; blend into creamed mixture. Divide batter in half. Blend together cocoa powder and melted butter; stir

into 1/2 of the dough. Spread cocoa dough evenly into prepared baking pan. Stir remaining 1/4 cup flour and 1/2 cup M&M's semi-sweet chocolate mini baking bits into remaining dough. Spread evenly over cocoa dough in pan. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup M&M's semi-sweet chocolate mini baking bits. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges start to pull away from sides of pan. Cool completely. Cut into bars. Store in tightly covered containers.

title: old fashioned amish cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend sugar, oil and margarine.
Stir in eggs and cream well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Will make a soft dough.
Roll into balls.
Roll the balls in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon.
Flatten with fork and bake 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix together thoroughly first 3 ingredients.
Then add eggs, oil, then buttermilk; mix well and spoon into muffin pans.
Makes a good many and batter can be kept in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: black forest pie
directions: Combine marshmallow cream, chocolate and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Gradually add cherry juice, blending until smooth. Fold in whipped cream and cherries.
Pour into crust.
Freeze; garnish with cherries.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until dough forms and beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 450° oven for 8 to10 minutes until golden. Mix margarine and garlic powder.
Brush on hot biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan building up slight edges.
Bake 10 minutes.
Place apple slices on warm crust, sprinkling with mixed sugar and cinnamon.
Blend sour cream and egg yolks.
Drizzle over top. Bake about 25 minutes, or until apples or edges are lightly browned.
Do not overbake.
Serve warm or cooled.

title: betsy's hot chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta per directions on package.
Drain and transfer to large bowl.
Add broccoli
to hot pasta.

title: layered overnight salad
directions: Place shredded lettuce in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with celery, water chestnuts and frozen peas.
Completely cover with the mayonnaise.
(The back of a spoon helps.) Sprinkle with sugar, seasoned salt and garlic powder.
Sprinkle with cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, sprinkle with grated hard-boiled egg and bacon.
Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: red hot apples
directions: Peel and core apples.
Place in microwave baking dish (with holes up).
Add water.
Fill holes with sugar (sugar will dissolve into water), then fill holes with red hots.
Save unused red hots to add later.
Bake 5 minutes on High setting.
Turn apples over and baste thoroughly.
Add red hots to holes.
Bake 5 minutes; turn and baste.
Continue this cycle until apples are bright through and through.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir together remaining ingredients. Add dry mixture gradually to other bowl and mix well.
Spray Pam into mini-muffin tins and spoon in batter to 3/4 full. Bake at 400° F. for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions. Add broccoli for last 4 minutes of cooking time. Drain. Heat butter in skillet. Add chicken and cook until browned, stirring often. Add soup, milk, cheese, pepper and linguine mixture and heat through. Serve with additional parmesan cheese. Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together all but cheese and potato chips.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover top with 1/2 cup shredded cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: green beans in olive oil (lubiyeh bi-zaut)
directions: Wash beans in cold water, cut off ends and cut in half.
Chop onions and garlic and saute them in oil until golden.
Add beans, salt and allspice and toss lightly.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes over low heat; add tomato paste.
Slice tomatoes and fold in; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes until it thickens.
Can be served cold or hot.
Serves 4.

title: white chili
directions: Combine beans, stock, 2 cups onion, garlic and salt in heavy saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 hours, until beans are tender, adding more stock as needed.
When beans are tender, add remaining 2 cups onions, chilies and all seasonings.
Mix well and continue to cook 30 minutes.
Just before serving, add cooked chicken and heat thoroughly.
To serve, place 1 1/2 cups of chili in a bowl; top with cheese.
Serves 8.

title: sheer joy grits
directions: Bring 1 1/2 cups water to boil.
Add grits, 4 tablespoons butter, salt and sugar.
Cook until liquid has been absorbed and grits cooked.
Stir frequently.
Add eggs, milk and cheese.
Pour into 2-quart well-greased casserole.
Top with additional cheese and butter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
(I use garlic cheese.)

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread in rectangular pan with fingers. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces, then flour meat, salt and pepper (to taste) and add a small piece of garlic.
Brown meat in grease in pan.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add oil, buttermilk and eggs.
Mix well again.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 72 muffins.
Batter may be refrigerated and baked a few at a time.
Serve warm with butter and jelly.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Layer corn bread, bacon, onions, peppers and tomatoes. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sweet pickles.
Combine mayonnaise with pickle juice and sugar.
Drizzle over salad and toss before serving.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix the flour, brown sugar and shortening well.
Take out 1 cup for tops.
In remainder, add the syrup, eggs and baking soda. Mix real good.
Pour into the pie crusts. Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed pepper pot
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of pepper and remove seed.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish combine onion and ground beef.
Place in microwave and cook 2 to 3 minutes on High or until beef is slightly brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except peppers.
Mix well. Stuff peppers with mixture and place on baking sheet.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave 12 to 15 minutes on Medium-high.
Make sure baking sheet is microwavable.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam) with 1 package crescent rolls.
Press together.
Mix the cream cheese, 2/3 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and egg yolk.
Pour over top of the crescent rolls, then top it off with the other can of rolls.
Mix nuts, 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top.
Finish off by pouring egg white over nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown meat and onion.
Add sauce and cook together for 5 minutes.
Grease casserole dish and pour all ingredients in.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and beans
directions: Brown the ground beef and chopped onion; drain.
Add pork and beans, mushrooms, ketchup, chili powder, water and salt and pepper.
Mix and let simmer about 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat margarine and peanut butter on high for 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 cup flour, sugars, egg, baking powder, soda and vanilla.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Stir in remaining flour and peanuts.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Drain pineapple, but save juice for glaze.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together and set aside.
Beat the butter and sugar together, then add eggs and keep beating.
Next, add the pineapple, vanilla and sifted ingredients.
Mix well and chill. Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes, then while still warm spoon glaze over cookies.

title: beef shepherds pie
directions: In large heavy ovenproof skillet, heat the oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute over medium heat until tender.
Add beef and cook until browned.
Drain fat.
Add salt, pepper, broth, peas and carrots.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring once to break up vegetables.
Mix the flour with Worcestershire sauce until smooth. Stir into the meat mixture.
Spread the mashed potatoes over the top.
Make criss-cross markings with fork.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: creamy potato puffs
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and potatoes, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in a 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cut or tear bread into small pieces and combine with pineapple; mix well.
Put in a medium size bowl.
Beat eggs, sugar, margarine and milk; pour over bread and pineapple.
Mix well and pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed, then beat with mixer until smooth.
Grease and flour 3 bread loaf pans or 3 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Nuts, coconut and raisins are good optionals to use.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Drain.
Melt margarine, blend in flour and add oil and water.
Stir over heat until sauce boils and thickens.
Then stir in beaten egg, 1 teaspoon salt and grated cheese.
Stir until cheese melts. Arrange macaroni and cheese sauce in layers in a buttered casserole and bake in oven at 400° until toasted on top (10 to 15 minutes).
Makes 5 servings.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg yolks; beat well. Add lemon juice and flour; beat well. Add milk and beaten whites of eggs. Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch x 8-inch x 2-inch pan or pyrex dish. Mix sugar, milk and flour in separate bowl.
Pour this over butter.
Add pie fruit last.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until crust is golden brown.
Serves 8. (May sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top before crust browns, then allow to brown.)

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Pour over crumbled crackers and mix well.
Add fruits and nuts.
Put in cracker box and store in refrigerator.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Add soup, milk, tuna and onion.
Mix together and pour in baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Tuna may be substituted with corned beef and garden peas may be added.

title: lazy man pie
directions: Pour pie filling in dish. Cover with cake mix (dry) and then slice stick of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Then serve with ice cream.

title: janis' orange-pineapple jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple and sugar over medium heat in a saucepan until hot.
Add the box of orange jello and let set until cool.
Add the pecans, buttermilk and Cool Whip and stir thoroughly.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours, then enjoy!

title: peppers roasted
directions: Let most peppers turn red in garden, can use green too.
Pick peppers and place on grill.
Let cook until done.
Take pepper off grill.
Put in roaster with lid to keep warm.
Take out and let cool.
Peel off skin and split into 3 or 4 slices.
Pack into canning jars.
No water, they make their own juice.
Cold pack in roaster filled in water over jars.
Let cook 15 minutes or so once water and peppers start to boil.
Rinse peppers and strain (checking for skins).
Mix mixture over peppers.
Stir; taste. Keep in fridge.

title: french burger
directions: Mix hamburger with salt, Worcestershire sauce and onion. Split loaf of French bread and spread halves with hamburger mixture.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.
Broil last 5 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Alternate layers of raw potatoes, onions and cheese in a shallow casserole dish. Pour milk and soup over layers. Add butter, salt and pepper. Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hazel's alabama cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in greased pan at 450° for 25 or 30 minutes or until done.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix flour and 2 tablespoons of brown sugar.
With fingers, work in 1/2 cup butter until dough begins to hold together. Press into bottom of greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until just firm.

title: pineapple-apple crunch
directions: You will need a buttered baking dish.

title: hot spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons mixture in hot water.
Good in winter or when you have a cold.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 tsp. salt.
Mix well.
Add bag of chocolate chips and blend well.
In another medium bowl, sift together flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, 1/2 teaspoon salt and baking soda.
Add to dry ingredients, water, salad oil and vanilla. Blend well.
Using cupcake liners, line cupcake pans.
Fill each cup 1/2 full with the chocolate batter.
Drop 1 heaping teaspoonful of the cream cheese mixture into the middle of each chocolate filled cup.
Over the top of each cup, sprinkle slivered/sliced almonds and a little sugar.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.
These are very rich, but so wonderful.

title: party mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients and mix with sauce.
Bake in very slow oven at 275° for 1 hour.
Stir often.

title: 20 minute apple butter
directions: Boil hard for 20 minutes and can in pint cans.
Makes 7 pints.

title: glorified rice
directions: Combine cooked rice, pineapple, marshmallows, sugar and chopped apples.
Let stand 1 hour.
Whip cream; fold into mixture just before serving.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Mix everything together and put in a tube pan. Cook at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. When done, dump the cake and place in holes in top. While hot, pour this mixture over top; squeeze juice from 2 to 3 oranges and add 1 cup of confectioners sugar.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Serve on leaf of "butter lettuce".
Garnish with sprig of mint and one lychee.

title: broccoli sausage quiche
directions: Line the unbaked pie shell with a double thickness of foil. Bake in 450° oven for 8 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake 4 to 6 minutes more or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and set aside.
Reduce oven temperature to 375°.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, cook sausage and mushrooms about 5 minutes or until sausage is brown; drain.
In a medium bowl, stir together the eggs, soup, onion and pepper.
Stir in the sausage mixture, broccoli and 3/4 cup of the cheese.
Pour mixture into the baked shell and sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In medium saucepan, melt morsels and margarine.
Stir in crumbs and nuts. Press half of the mixture firmly onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: blueberry pie
directions: In prepared pie shell, bake in 425° oven for 40 minutes.

title: party pizza snacks
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
In saucepan place all ingredients and heat until cheese melts.
Place on rye bread.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Place flank steak in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Combine all ingredients and pour over steak.
Place in refrigerator and allow to marinate overnight, turning several times.
Excellent for barbecue; best if medium-rare.
Slice meat on the diagonal before serving.

title: easy oven beef stew
directions: Place raw meat in a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Add vegetables.
Blend salt, sugar and tapioca.
Sprinkle over meat and vegies.
Add tomato juice.
Cover pan with foil, sealing tight around edges. Bake at 250° for 4 hours.
If it gets too thick, add water.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hungarian meat roll
directions: Combine eggs, bread, juice, seasonings and garlic to ground beef.
Prepare foil (13 x 10) and spread ground beef mixture within about an inch of the foil.
Arrange ham in the middle and sprinkle half the cheese over it.
Beginning with the short end, roll the meat, lifting the foil as you go and seal the edges of the meat on all sides.
Discard foil.
Bake in a 13 x 9 baking dish at 350° for one hour.
Add remaining cheese on top for an additional fifteen minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Add drained sauerkraut.
Cut up corned beef in small pieces.
Toss together.
Add mixture of mayonnaise, ketchup and dill.
Top with the cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and brown.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Wash rice thoroughly.
Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into small balls.
Heat tomato soup and water in a pressure cooker.
Drop meatballs into soup mixture.
Cover pressure cooker.
Allow steam to flow from vent pipe to release air.
Place indicater weight on vent pipe; cook for 10 minutes at 15 pounds pressure.
Yields 6 servings.

title: quick turkey roll-ups
directions: Mix both soups with milk; add some to bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Now make stuffing mix.
Add 1 tablespoon stuffing to a piece of lunch meat; roll lunch meat up and put cut side down in pan. Do this until pan is full.
Add rest of soup and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You will have turkey and stuffing; add mashed potatoes and a vegetable.

title: 3 day coconut cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box.
Cook in 2 layers. Let cake cool thoroughly.
Split layers into 4 layers.
Mix coconut with sour cream and sugar.
Set aside 1/2 cup of this. Spread between layers of cake.
Mix 1/2 cup of mixture with whipped topping and spread on top and sides.
Refrigerate 3 days, then serve.

title: chicken avocado salad
directions: Combine the avocado,
olives, celery, chicken, salt and the eggs and mix carefully with the mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring broth and cooked rice to boil.
Beat eggs and lemon juice in bowl just long enough to combine.
Pour broth over eggs, gradually stirring constantly, allowing eggs to shred but not curdle.
Serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices and arrange on cookie sheet or cake pan, overlapping slightly.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Let cool.
Combine juices from pineapple and oranges (or orange juice) to make about 1 1/2 to 2 cups.
Stir in two tablespoons cornstarch and cook.
Stir constantly until thick. Cool.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip and spoon on cooled crust. Arrange fruits on top of cheese and Cool Whip mixture.
Use pineapple chunks, mandarin oranges, halved strawberries, sliced kiwi, halved grapes, banana slices, etc.
Pour fruit juice mixture over fruit.
Cover well (especially bananas).
Chill.
Cut in squares and enjoy.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: rich flaky pie shell
directions: Stir
flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together.

Cut in shortening and butter with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly. Add water, a little at a time, using just enough to bind mixture so that dough can be patted lightly to form a ball. Handle as little as possible. This makes enough for three 9-inch single shells.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour.
Blend until smooth.
Add milk.
Add vegetables (peas, carrots, celery and potatoes) and chicken.
Pour into crust and bake 1 hour.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased skillet. Bake in oven at 350° until done in center.
Serves 7 to 8.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage and drain off grease.
Mix the mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in sausage, cheese and pepper.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cocoa.
Beat yolks in small mixer bowl with 1/2 cup sugar until thick and lemon colored. Beat in chocolate mixture, rum and vanilla.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Wash and pare carrots.
Cut in 1/4-inch thick sticks.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender.
Combine remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling point.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack carrots in hot sterilized jars.
Pour vinegar mixture over carrots and seal.

title: spiral cinnamon raisin bread
directions: Heat milk until bubbles form.
Remove and add 1/4 cup sugar, salt, 1/2 cup butter and raisins. Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast with 1/2 cup warm water. Stir milk mixture in with yeast. Add eggs and 4 cups flour. Beat with a wooden spoon 2 minutes.
Add last of the flour. With hand, mix until dough is stiff. Turn dough onto floured board.
Knead 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl. Turn dough over so greased side is up. Cover with towel and let rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer, after previously softening cheese and butter.
Serve with crackers.

title: pea and peanut
directions: Combine.
Let set overnight or 2 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dust strips of beef with flour, salt and pepper.
Melt margarine in heavy skillet and saute mushrooms and onions.
When tender, remove and set aside.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Mix flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper together.
Coat meat with flour mixture.
Melt shortening in large skillet; brown meat thoroughly.
Add water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 hours.
Stir in remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes longer, or until vegetables are tender.
If desired, thicken stew. In a covered jar, shake 1 cup cold water with 2 to 4 tablespoons flour until blended.
Stir into stew.
Heat to boiling; stirring constantly, boil 1 minute.
Serves 6.

title: noah's ark sugar cookies
directions: You will also need clear nylon fishing line.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in an 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the water, cinnamon and salt.
Work the sugar, flour and soft margarine together until crumbly.
Spread crumb mixture over apples.
Bake, uncovered, 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Put the Butt or shoulder in a crock-pot.
Cover and cook at 325° for 7 hours or until done.
Do not add any liquids.
It makes its own!
Prepare the barbecue sauce by thoroughly mixing the remaining ingredients.
If necessary, refrigerate until needed.
When meat is done, place it on a platter or cutting board to cool.
Clean the crock-pot.
Remove the bone and scrape the fat off the meat.
Tear it into strips.
Put the strips into the crock-pot and pour the sauce on top of the meat.
Mix the meat and sauce well.
Cover and cook at 325° for 3 hours.
Makes 12 generous servings.

title: fern's apple butter
directions: Bring to a boil and cook so it thickens somewhat.

title: bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Blend well.
In saucepan, heat water and oil until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquid to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in an additional 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour until dough pulls cleanly away from sides of bowl.
On floured surface, knead in 1/2 to 1 cup flour until dough is smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel.
Let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until light and doubled in size, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down dough several times to remove all air bubbles.
Divide dough in half; shape into balls. Allow to rest on counter, covered with inverted bowl for 15 minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves by rolling dough into two 14 x 7-inch loaves.
Cover; let rise in warm place until dough is 1-inch above pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pepper cons(snack)
directions: Mix sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and hot water.
Mix all dry ingredients together; gradually stir into mixture.
Bake at 375°.
Use smallest measuring spoon and roll into a ball.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 11 minutes.
After they cool, place them in an airtight container or in a
jar with a lid.

title: "souper-burgers"
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown the ground beef and onions, stirring to separate meat.
Drain excess fat.
Add the vegetable soup, catsup, mustard and pepper.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until brown, stirring occasionally.
Serve on warm or buttered buns.

title: strawberry bavarian in chocolate shell
directions: PIE SHELL:
Melt chocolate chips in margarine, over hot not boiling water.
Line pie plate with foil and spread melted chocolate.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Slowly peel off foil.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding as instructed on box with 3 c. milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put layer of crackers in a
9 x 13 inch pan.
Spread 1/2 of pudding mixture, then second layer of crackers,
then remaining pudding and top with layer of crackers.

title: hummas (bean dip)
directions: Shell Garbanzo beans if you want a finer consisitancy. Squeeze lemons and add all ingredients in food processor.
Add liquid from beans to make dip the consistency you want.

title: cheddar-bacon spread
directions: Cook bacon; drain on paper towels.
Crumble and set aside. In blender at medium speed, or in food processor with knife blade attached, blend cheese and next 4 ingredients until smooth. Stir in crumbled bacon.
Cover and refrigerate, if not serving right away.
To serve, bring spread to room temperature to soften slightly.
Serve with party rye bread.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add garlic and cook 1 minute.
(Do not brown.)
Stir in flour and mix well.
Add clams with liquid, salt, basil and pepper.
Heat to a boil, reduce and simmer 5 minutes.
Add parsley.
Serve with 8 ounces pasta and Parmesan cheese.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° until done.

title: play clay christmas ornaments
directions: In medium saucepan, stir cornstarch and baking soda.

Add all water and stir until smooth. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches the consistency of slightly dry mashed potatoes. Mixture will come to a boil, then start to thicken.
Turn onto plate and cover with a damp cloth.
Cool. When cool enough to handle, knead until smooth and pliable on surface dusted with cornstarch.
Makes 20 ornaments.
Cut one at a time.
Keep dough stored in plastic bag.

title: white trash
directions: Mix cereal, raisins and nuts in large container.
Melt chocolate chips, oleo and peanut butter over low heat.
Pour over cereal mixture and stir until coated.
In a large plastic bag, pour powdered sugar, then cereal mix.
Shake until coated with powdered sugar.
Store in a covered tin.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cabbage and tomato sauce or bouillon.
Put about 1/4 cup mixture in each cabbage leaf and roll up.
Place in freezer, wrapped, in a baking dish.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Bring water, butter and milk to a boil.
Add instant potatoes, salt, onion and pepper; mix well.
Amount of instant potatoes depends on your desired thickness.
Add diced potatoes; simmer until hot and desired thickness.
Serve and top with parsley flakes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Blend cheese and mayonnaise with sugar.
Add fruit, nuts and cream.
Pour into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Freeze six hours. Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Slice and serve on lettuce.
Serves 8 to 10.
Really good and very attractive.

title: lebkuchen cookies
directions: Add marmalade and honey to the eggs.
Beat well.
Add all dry ingredients together and then stir into the egg mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan 20 minutes at 350°.
When cool, cut into bars and use a powdered sugar and milk frosting or sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until lemon colored.
Add pineapple; stir in bread.
Put in buttered dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour, until golden brown.

title: whoopy pie cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and liquid; mix well.
Drop onto cookie sheet by tablespoon or whatever size cookies you prefer.

title: aunt lee's chinese chicken casserole
directions: Mix the cream of chicken soup, 1 can water, mayonnaise and lemon juice together first.
Add to other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into long, shallow baking dish; top with chopped cashew nuts or sliced almonds.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and paprika in 2 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Add egg and beat.
Add creamed corn and 1/2 cup crumbs, salt and pepper to taste.
Layer in a 1 1/2-quart casserole, starting with broccoli, then half corn mixture and 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Repeat to get two layers.
Top with other 1/4 cup crumbs and remaining tablespoon of butter, melted.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vanishing peanut butter squares(makes 9 servings)
directions: Finely roll 20 cookies.
In small bowl, mix cookie crumbs and margarine.
Press on bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Chill.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter.
Add egg; beat smoothly.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brownies
directions: Melt the chocolate and butter slowly; cool.
Beat eggs well and add sugar gradually.
Continue to beat and put in chocolate. Fold vanilla, flour, salt and nuts.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for about 30 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick.
Cut after brownies have been out of oven for about 30 minutes.

title: egg sausage bake
directions: Put cubed bread and Velveeta cheese in a large mixing bowl. Add browned sausage to large bowl.
Add milk, prepared mustard and black pepper to beaten eggs; pour over first 3 ingredients.
Mix and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Uncover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs well, one at a time.
Add sugar and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and add. Beat well.
Cook in 350° oven.
While hot, sprinkle marshmallows and nuts on top.

title: madeleine's cobbler
directions: Place butter in an 8 x 10 x 2 inch baking pan.
Place in warm oven to melt.
In a bowl sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
Stir in milk and blend until smooth.
Turn into baking pan over the melted butter.
Spread with the fruit and bake at 375 for 40 minutes or until topping is browned and crisp. Serve with ice cream.

title: skillet pizza
directions: Use electric skillet at 375° or stove top skillet on high, greased.
Mix crust as directed.
Put crust into skillet.
Turn to medium heat.
Add sauce and seasonings, then add toppings.
Cook 15 minutes or until crust is brown and cheese is melted.

title: substitute for eagle brand milk
directions: Blend well in blender; store in refrigerator.
This will work well in any recipe.

title: pecan cheese log
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Add pecans.
Mix well.
Shape into log.
Sprinkle finely chopped pecans on top.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Combine mix, water and tomatoes in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add shrimp and simmer 20 minutes; salt to taste.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve over hot cooked rice. Yield: 6 servings.

title: chewies
directions: Mix together.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Blend together first 8 ingredients.
Layer shrimp, onions and bay leaves in bowl.
Pour sauce over all and cover.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Serve in bowl with toothpicks or spear onto decorative picks and push into half head of red cabbage.
Serves about 20 guests.

title: merlene's cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to egg and oil mixture. Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop 1 teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes in 350° oven.

title: icebox cheese wafers
directions: Cream together the cheese, butter, salt and pepper; add flour. Make into a roll; wrap in waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator. When ready to bake, slice into thin wafers.
Bake in moderate oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen wafers.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut butter in dry ingredients with fork or
pie
blender.
Beat
egg
and
milk
together.
Dust blueberries with 1 tablespoon
flour.
Add egg and milk to dry ingredients; fold in blueberrries.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Grease Bundt or tube pan and place biscuits into pan.
In saucepan, melt and mix butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour mixture over biscuits and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: raisin-n-carrots
directions: Mix ingredients and put to chill.
Serve.

title: meat pie
directions: Use stove top to oven-safe stock pot or large casserole dish.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook butter, sugar and water (260°); stir constantly.
Add almonds; continue cooking to 300° (hard crack stage).
Stir continually; remove from heat. Add vanilla; pour into buttered pan.
Cut up chocolate and put on top of candy while hot.
As chocolate melts, spread evenly over candy.
Sprinkle grated almonds over top.
When chocolate is hard, it's ready to eat.

title: chocolate marvel pie
directions: Melt and blend over hot water the chocolate chips, milk and sugar.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Add 3 egg yolks, one at a time. Beat well after each addition. Add the vanilla.
Beat 3 egg whites until stiff. Add a little of the egg whites to the chocolate mixture.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: savory chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine
ingredients
in large saucepan. Cover and cook for 5 minutes.

title: one-rise cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, 2 tablespoons butter, egg and 1 cup hot water in mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining 2 cups flour.
Knead on floured surface 1 minute.
Roll 7 x 15-inch rectangle.
Spread mixture of 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 cup butter over dough. Roll as for jelly roll.
Slice.
Combine cream, brown sugar and walnuts in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place rolls in prepared pan. Let rise for 35 to 45 minutes or until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 35 minutes or until brown.
Cool for 15 minutes before inverting on serving tray.
Makes 16 servings.

title: pepper tomato relish
directions: Put green tomatoes, sweet peppers and onions through a food chopper.
Put in large pot and boil them for 15 minutes, then remove from heat and add salt.
Boil again for 15 minutes.
Stir often so the mixture doesn't stick.
Drain through a colander and add the following ingredients:
vinegar, sugar, cinnamon, allspice and whole cloves.
Boil the mixture rapidly, then add celery seed and mustard seed.
Put into clean jars and seal.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni in three quarts of water. Drain.
Use a two quart casserole coated with Pam.
Cover the bottom with 15 crushed crackers.
Divide the macaroni in half for the second layer.
Use 8 ounces of cubed or shredded cheese for next layer.
Sprinkle over this black pepper.
Distribute 1/2 stick margarine now.
Repeat the layers.
Top with another layer of crackers, butter (1/2 stick) and pepper.
Heat milk.
Pour over the top until you can see on edges.
Let set 5 minutes.
Check to see the milk; if not, add more milk.
Bake 45 minutes or until hot in center or crackers are brown.

title: thimble cookies
directions: Cream butter and
sugar
until
smooth.
Add beaten egg yolk, flavoring and flour.
Shape into small balls the size of a small walnut.
Dip
in egg white and then into nuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Make a dent in dough with a thimble or something similar.
Bake
in 350° oven for 5 minutes, take out
and
dent again.
Bake
approximately
minutes more. Remove from oven and fill dent with jam while hot.

title: pasole with pork
directions: Place pork and water in a saucepan and cook, covered, until meat is tender (1 hour).
Drain hominy.
Add remaining ingredients, tasting for salt.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Wrap each chicken breast in a slice of bacon, spiraling it to cover breast, and secure with a toothpick.
Place dried beef in the bottom of casserole dish, layering it to cover bottom.
Place chicken breasts on top of beef.
Mix undiluted soup and sour cream; spoon over chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 250° oven for 3 hours.

title: chicken marsala
directions: In a large frying pan, melt 2 tablespoons butter over medium heat.
Add chicken and saute, turning once, until lightly browned, about 2 minutes on each side.
Remove; set aside.

title: baked pork and beans casserole
directions: Pour pork and beans into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Add brown sugar and onion; add catsup.
Top with bacon. Bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: turkey skillet dinner
directions: Combine and simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave confectioners sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo on High (full power) until butter melts, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir until smooth. Blend in vanilla and nuts.
Spread into buttered 8-inch square pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cream of tomato soup with parmesan cheese
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add all ingredients except cheese.
Top with cover and pulse until mixture is smooth. Pour mixture into a saucepan; cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Stir in cheese; heat until cheese melts.

title: smoked sausage and potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.

Peel and slice onion 1/4-inch thick. Boil until potatoes and onion become transparent, but not completely done. Drain potatoes and onion. Layer potatoes and onion mixture in bottom of casserole dish. Slice smoked sausage 1/2-inch thick.
Layer smoked sausage in casserole dish.
Add a layer of grated cheese. Continue layering, finishing with grated cheese on top. Bake, covered, at 350° until smoked sausage is done.
Uncover and bake until edges are brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in bouillon until done; cut as for salad. Cook spaghetti in broth until it takes up all the broth. Brown the celery, onions and pepper in butter until they wither. Add to tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, chicken, spaghetti, cheese and mushroom soup in large, flat baking dish. Mix well. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Even better after reheated.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker pie crust. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: butterscotch cheese cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In saucepan, melt morsels and margarine.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press half the mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add condensed milk, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Top with remainder of crumb mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill and cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: eileen's chili
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Mix dry ingredients and add to meat. Chop tomatoes and add to meat with the water.
Heat 15 to 20 minutes, covered.
Simmer for a long time (at least 5 hours).
A half hour before serving, add chili beans.
Serve with bowls of onions and grated sharp Cheddar cheese on the side.

title: beef pies
directions: Cook meat, onions and green chilies. Drain off fat. Add soups and tomatoes. Flatten biscuits. Put in cupcake pan and add a spoon of meat mixture. Top with cheese (optional). Spray pan before putting biscuits in. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: david's spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook and drain beef.
In large skillet, saute garlic, onions, peppers, olives and mushrooms.
Add beef and tomatoes, sauce and paste.
Let simmer on medium to low heat for 2 hours.

title: dilly beans
directions: Wash beans and remove ends.
Cut beans into 2-inch pieces and divide among 7 hot, sterile pint jars.
Put 1/4 teaspoon red pepper, 1/2 teaspoon pickling spices, 1/2 teaspoon dill and 1 clove garlic into each jar.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour boiling mixture over beans, leaving 1/2-inch headroom. Seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: holiday sugar roll out cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and flavorings.
Mix well. Fold in dry ingredients, blending well.
Chill 3 to 4 hours. Roll out and cut as desired.
Bake on lightly greased sheet at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Frost if desired.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cut cheese into pieces and place in large mixing bowl; beat 1 minute.
Add eggs and egg yolk and mix well.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Add vanilla and cream and beat until smooth.

Place into prepared crust; bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 250° and bake for 45 to 65 minutes or until cake is slightly browned, has risen and is cooked on top. Cool to room temperature, then refrigerate overnight.

title: beef and cheese noodle bake
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Then add 1 package onion soup mix.
Boil the egg noodles and drain.
In a baking dish, place in ground beef and cooked egg noodles.
Add some Mozzarella cheese and stir so it melts.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup.
Stir it together and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350°
for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fried chicken fingers
directions: Wash and drain chicken breasts.
Cut into long fingers.
Mix egg and milk in small bowl.
Mix flour and Mrs. Dash in shaking bag.
Dip chicken fingers in egg and milk mixture and then shake in flour bag until well coated.
Fry chicken 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix jello and water. Let set for a little, then add pineapple, celery, horseradish, mayo and cottage cheese.
Nuts and pimento are optional.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Cream together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of each mini muffin cup.
Spoon 1 teaspoon creamed mixture into muffin cups.

title: delicious southern biscuits
directions: Combine self-rising flour and cold lard.
Add baking powder. Cut in until mealy.
Add buttermilk.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Flour your counter or tabletop and roll biscuit mixture into a ball.
Knead gently 8 to 12 times.
Roll out and cut about 1/2 inch thick.
Melt a cup of butter and dip each cut biscuit into the butter.
Place on a baking sheet and bake at 400° about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: killer barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil for approximately 5 minutes over medium heat or lower temperature and cook slower for a more savory sauce.

title: muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Fill 12 greased medium muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serve warm

title: root beer
directions: Mix ingredients in a gallon jar, then fill jar with warm water.
Set in sun, not over 3 hours.

title: peach crisp
directions: Put peaches and their juice in bottom of baking dish. Sprinkle dry cake mix over this.
Add melted butter; spread evenly to cover dry cake mix.
Sprinkle nut meats.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until slightly browned.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: meat loaves(large-quantity recipe)
directions: Combine meat, onions,
celery
and
garlic.
Add
bread crumbs, salt, pepper, slightly
beaten
eggs
and
stock.
Mix well but do not over-handle.
Mold	into
loaves
the width of baking pans, 3-inches high and 4-inches wide.
Brush tops with bacon fat.	Bake, uncovered,
and
without water, in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until
desired doneness is reached.	Do not overcook.
Strained pan juices may be made into gravy with any favorite recipe.
Yields 50 servings, 5 ounces each.

title: country captain chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Remove to a baking dish.
In same pan, cook onion, pepper and garlic until limp.
Stir in chicken broth and salt.
Pour over chicken in baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Stir in almonds and currants.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon on top.
Serve with rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: supreme beef casserole(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Lightly grease a 2-quart casserole.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter and confectioners sugar together well, then add margarine.
Mix well, then shape into small ball shapes.
Melt coating (no paraffin needed) over warm water until consistency to dip centers.
Microwave can be used to melt chocolate.
Place dipped buckeyes on wax paper to let chocolate set up.
Store at 70° for up to 3 days or in fridge for longer periods.

title: taco salad - low-fat
directions: Prepare tortilla cups; set aside.
Prepare tomatillo guacamole; cover and chill.
In a medium skillet cook beef and garlic until beef is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in kidney beans, corn, taco sauce and chili powder.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Prepare figs for cooking; chop.
Mix first 3 ingredients together and cook 20 minutes.
Add 3 boxes jello and cook for 2 minutes more.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with banana, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts. Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm with butter or cool for later.

title: daddy's night to cook chili
directions: Thaw turkey completely.
Drain all water.
Rub butter outside (best to use squeeze Parkay).
Coat real heavy with Tony's Cajun spices.
Put spices inside and outside the turkey.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: easy blackberry jam cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix the first seven ingredients.
Put mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Chop nuts; sprinkle over top and pat in.
Melt butter or margarine and drizzle over top of cake.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: quick praline bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange graham crackers in a single layer in ungreased jelly roll pan.
Heat brown sugar and margarine to boiling.
Boil and stir one minute; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over crackers; spread evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Cool slightly. Cut into 2 1/4 x 1 1/4-inch bars.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix ingredients well with enough broth to pour easily into greased pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: homemade waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
Mix until slightly lumpy. Bake in waffle iron.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream
butter
and sugar; add eggs and cream.
Mix soda with water and add to mixture.
Add salt and vanilla.
Stir in dates, cherries and pecans.
Add flour.
Drop teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° to 325° until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart bowl. Add syrup and mix well. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in next 3 ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli a little until unthawed; drain.
Add to remaining ingredients which have been mixed together well.
Put in a large casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Cover and refrigerate for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: In a covered 2-quart microwave-safe dish, cook bacon on High for 4 or 5 minutes or until crisp. Remove with a slotted spoon to drain. Set aside. Drain clam juice into the drippings. Stir in potatoes and onion; cover and cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring once or twice. Stir flour into 1/4 cup of milk and add to potato mixture. Stir in salt, pepper and remaining milk. Cover and cook on Medium for 6 minutes, stirring once or twice. Let stand for 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in clams and butter. Garnish with bacon and parsley.

title: vegetable confetti
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to directions and drain well. Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend celery soup, milk, sour cream and cheese in large bowl.
Lightly stir into vegetables.
Transfer mixture into a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.

title: cream cheese apple bars
directions: Blend together butter, 2/3 cup sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes. Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar. Add 1 egg at a time and mix. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour over crust. Spread apple filling over top and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Shut off oven, keeping bars in oven until it cools. Remove and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: oatmeal buns
directions: Combine oatmeal, boiling water and margarine. Cool to lukewarm. Add sugars, salt and yeast. Knead in flour. Let rise and form into dinner rolls. Let rise and bake 20-30 minutes.

title: 24 hour brisket
directions: Twenty-four hours ahead, place brisket (fat side up) in a heavy foil or a covered baking dish.
Pour coffee over brisket; seal or cover and bake in a preheated 200° oven for 24 hours. When it has baked 24 hours, remove from oven; pour off all the liquid and discard it.
Place meat on cutting board and trim off all the excess fat.
Slice brisket into strips.
Put brisket back into pan.
In a mixing bowl, combine and mix together all the remaining ingredients and pour this sauce over the brisket.
Bake at 200° for at least 1 more hour.
It freezes beautifully.

title: mother's strawberry jello dessert
directions: In a small saucepan, melt oleo.
Stir in crumbs.
Put firmly on bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Chill.

title: cream cheese frosting(club member: christy hosey)
directions: Mix all medium speed.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Combine ground chuck, eggs, crumbs, onion, salt and pepper in a bowl; mix.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown in hot oil in skillet, turning to brown all sides.
Remove meatballs (not thoroughly cooked).
Reserve 2 tablespoons pan drippings in skillet.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to measure 1 1/4 cups liquid mix.
Mix cornstarch, 1/4 cup pineapple/water mixture, soy sauce, vinegar, brown sugar and catsup with reserved drippings in skillet.
Simmer until thickened, stirring frequently. Add meatballs, pineapple chunks and green pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Brown flour in oil in large heavy pot slowly, stirring to make mahogany brown roux. Add chopped vegetables and saut until soft. Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, chicken stock, water, okra and seasoning. Stir and simmer about 45 minutes. Add seafood and cook another 20 to 30 minutes. Serve around scoop of hot rice. Offer file at table. Serves 8 to 10.

title: danish cucumber salad
directions: Cut cucumbers into thin slices (can be done with a potato peeler).
Chop parsley and put over cucumbers.
Mix vinegar, sugar and salt until sugar is dissolved.
Add a little water (this will depend on how strong you like the liquid).
Pour over cucumbers and mix.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours before serving.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Boil together first five ingredients for a minute.
Then let mixture cool.
Combine cabbage, carrot and salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze all liquid from vegetables and pack into jars or plastic freezer boxes.
Cover with vinegar mixture.
Freeze.
It will last six months at zero degrees.
Thaw in the refrigerator.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients
together except Mozzarella cheese.
Put half of the mixture in a long loaf pan. Put cheese on mixture. Put the rest of the hamburger mixture on top and pinch edges together
so cheese doesn't run out.
Pour rest of pizza sauce on top. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine chips, cheese, onions, tomatoes and lettuce.
Combine cooked and drained ground beef with the kidney beans.
Warm.
Combine chips, cheese, onions, tomatoes and lettuce mixture with ground beef and kidney beans and mix well.
Can be served with picante sauce.

title: apple chicken salad
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water until softened; add hot broth, onion juice, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Stir until gelatin dissolves.
Pour into mold; chill until thick.
Stir in pimento, celery and chicken.
Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: quick egg pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour over broke up bread and cut margarine over top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Mix; will be thick.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
While hot, spread with 1 cup chocolate chips; let melt, then spread evenly.
Top with 1 cup powdered sugar, 1/2 cup chunky peanut butter and 4 to 8 tablespoons milk.
Mix together and drizzle over top.

title: zucchini patties or fritters
directions: Grate zucchini;
add
salt
and
let
stand for 1 hour. Drain zucchini well.
Add the rest of the ingredients and drop by tablespoon	into
1 inch of hot oil.
Let cook until brown. You can sprinkle extra cheese on them if you want to.
This is very good with syrup.

title: deer meat stew
directions: Cut enough deer meat into small cubes to fill half of a crock-pot.
Add garlic, Worcestershire sauce, onion, garlic salt, Creole salt, pepper and regular salt to taste.
Add green onions, potatoes and carrots to 3/4 full.
Cook overnight in slow cooker.

title: chicken pougui (pookee)
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter with oil in heavy large saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and thyme; saute until soft, about 4 minutes. Add wine and cook until reduced in half.
Add soup and half and half. Stir until heated.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Blend until smooth.
Makes 1 small can.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Thoroughly combine sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk and mashed bananas.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake in moderate gas oven at 350°
for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cauliflower casserole a la astoria
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the cauliflower flowerets in an 11 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour on the broth.
Sprinkle the minced tomato, oregano, salt and pepper over the cauliflower.
Add the Feta cheese and toss well. Cover the pan with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Remove the foil and continue baking until the cauliflower is very tender, 30 minutes longer.
Toss the bread crumbs with the olive oil.
Sprinkle the crumbs over the cauliflower.
Bake until the crumbs are golden brown, an additional 30 minutes.
Serve 4.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine rice, eggs, Parmesan cheese, oregano and garlic powder.
Spread in pan. Bake for 10 minutes until firm.
Spread spaghetti sauce over rice. Top with Mozzarella cheese and anything else you would like. Continue baking 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: holiday ribbon ring
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello into 2 1/2 cups of boiling water. Pour 1 1/2 cups into 6-cup ring mold.
Chill until set.
Add 1/2 cup of yogurt to remaining jello.
Stir and spoon over jello in mold.
Chill.
Repeat with lime jello.
Chill at least 2 hours. Unmold.

title: imitation crab salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and set aside.
Chop crab in bite size chunks.
Chop scallion fine.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Let it sit to mingle.

title: joy's marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, parsley, salt, pepper, sugar and lemon juice in a huge Mason jar or anything that has a cover.
Add garlic clove (still intact) and mushrooms.
Cover and marinate several days or hours in the refrigerator.
Remove garlic and serve.
Serves 12.

title: date bars
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy with rotary beater. Sift together sugar, flour, baking powder, and salt. Stir into the beaten eggs. Add dates and nuts, mix until well blended.

title: company potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine the potatoes, sour cream, 1 c. cheese, carrot, onion, parsley, salt, dill, and pepper. Transfer to a greased 8 inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with the paprika and remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25-35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator and serve.

title: green chili and tomato salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add salt, tomatoes and green chilies; cool.
Add celery and green pepper.
Pour mixture into gelatin mold.
Refrigerate.
Serve with lettuce and mayonnaise, if desired.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add flour; stir until smooth. Add milk slowly and stir until mixture is thickened.
Add chicken broth and frozen broccoli.
Cook until broccoli is tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: olive and cream cheese spread
directions: Mix well the softened cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Add chopped olives and chopped pecans; stir well with 2 tablespoons olive juice and a dash of pepper.
Chill for 24 to 48 hours before serving.

title: aunt ab's tea cakes
directions: Use enough plain flour to make a good dough.
Mix all the other ingredients in until the dough can be rolled.
Roll out very thin and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 350° until brown.
If you wish, sprinkle sugar on top before baking.

title: spugety and meatballs
directions: Put the nodols is a pot with the sose and cook it for 2 minits.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the oil, sugar and eggs with a spoon.
Beat at medium speed until creamy.
Sift and measure the flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Combine ingredients and beat with mixer 2 minutes. Add vanilla.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Grease and flour pan. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and peanut butter. Mix well.
Add oatmeal, chips and M&M's.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven. (No flour in this recipe!)

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind both peppers up fine, seeds and all.
Boil sugar and vinegar for 1 minute; add pectin while boiling.
Let set a few minutes; strain through cheesecloth.
Add green food coloring.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
except half of the coconut. Form into balls and roll in remaining coconut.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In Dutch oven, heat vegetable oil over medium heat.
Add onions; saute for 2 minutes.
Add garlic and cook for 2 minutes. Add beef and cook until brown.
Add 1 1/2 cups water and cook over medium heat for 40 minutes.
After 40 minutes, add remaining 3/4 cup water and tomato paste.
Mix until smooth and add: sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours over low heat until meat is tender.
Just before serving, remove Dutch oven from heat and stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato pudding(century-old recipe)
directions: Boil or bake potatoes in skin to preserve flavor.
Peel and mash potatoes and add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: recipe for salvation(our heavenly father)
directions: Cook feet until tender.
Take meat off bones and add chopped onions.
Put salt, pepper and a little vinegar in a pan and bring to a boil.
Pour over meat and onion mixture and cool.

title: plain cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and eggs until light.
Add flour, milk, baking powder and flavoring and beat well.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut chicken in strips or chunks. (Serves 8.)
Top with cheese in casserole.
Mix soup and wine until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Toss stuffing with butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: no-fry doughnuts
directions: In a large mixing bowl dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, spices, eggs, shortening and 2 cups flour.
Blend 30 seconds on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour, scraping sides of bowl.
Cover, let rise in a warm place 50 - 60 minutes.
Turn dough onto well floured cloth covered board; roll out lightly to coat with flour.
Roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness, cut with 2 1/2 inch doughnut cutter.
Place 2 inches apart on baking sheet, brush with melted butter.
Cover for 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 425 and bake 8 - 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Immediately brush with melted butter and shake on sugar and cinnamon.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, then flour.
Mash bananas and add to other batter.
Sprinkle nuts with small amount of flour, then add to other mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: 1 2 3 party cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature for 1 hour, then mix the dry Ranch mix with it. (You will need to knead it very thoroughly for full flavor.) Form a round ball with this mixture. Roll your cheese ball in the chopped nuts (or paprika) and serve with your favorite snack cracker. This also makes a great spread for celery.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Boil 3 cups water; stir in jello and pudding and cook until slightly thickened.
Cool.
Fold whipped topping and oranges into mixture.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry christmas wreaths
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Prepare, bake and cool cake following package directions for basic recipe.

title: goody salad
directions: Dissolve the 2 jellos in the boiling water.
Mix all ingredients together; chill.
Frost with 1 cup sour cream.

title: lemon-angel dessert
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Mix egg
yolks, lemon juice, lemon rind and sugar.
Cook until spoon is coated.
Add gelatin. Cool.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add 3/4 cup sugar.
Fold into cooled custard.
Break 1/2 angel food cake into small pieces.
Put a layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish, then mix with custard until even and smooth.
Let stand until set.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in a large tube pan, 10-inch, for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and eggs; add dry ingredients.
Mix well; add cooked oatmeal.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bear's porridge
directions: Put water on to boil.
When boiling, add oatmeal and raisins, stirring well.
When thick, reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes.
Pour into bowls and add one teaspoon of peanut butter and honey.
Decorate with raisins.

title: orange-pineapple supreme
directions: Mix cake mix, Wesson oil, eggs, drained oranges and juice from pineapple; mix with mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add oil and vanilla; mix.
Add dry ingredients.
Add zucchini and mix.
Add raisins, coconut and nuts.
Mix.
Bake in a greased and floured pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves or 1 Bundt.

title: raspberry bars (mary carter)
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Press half of the crumb mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread on jam; sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.

title: potato cake
directions: Mix corn oil,
sugar,
flour,
spices,	baking	powder, salt, soda and potatoes.	Add
eggs,
one
at
a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla, nuts, raisins, coconut and fruit.
Pour
into	a greased tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours
or
longer.	Cake is best when allowed to mellow for a few days.

title: hickory log ribs
directions: Soak meat in vinegar for 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients and put on both sides of meat before grilling.
Cook on barbecue grill on slow fire.

title: ground meat and tomato gravy
directions: Season ground beef with Tony's seasoning.
Brown ground beef in pot.
Add onion and bell pepper; cook about 3 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and 1 can of water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and let simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Good with pork and beans as a side dish.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt together and blend. In another dish or pan, blend sugar, soft butter and vanilla. Then add your bananas, nuts, eggs and buttermilk to your dry ingredients.
Blend everything together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oysters salisbury
directions: Open oysters, letting remain in deep half of shell.
Melt butter in 1-quart saucepan, blend in flour and slowly add milk. Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the Swiss and Parmesan cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, nutmeg, pepper and salt.
Cook spinach and squeeze out excess moisture.
Blend spinach into cheese sauce and let mixture cool.
Top each oyster with 1 tablespoon spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Chop celery and green onions.
Boil until soft; drain.
Melt cheese and milk on low heat.
Add celery, whites of onions and peppers.
Heat and serve with tortilla chips.
(Like Casa Ole's!)

title: apple butter
directions: Cook 40 minutes.
Put in pint jars and seal.

title: fiddleheads with chardonnay and bacon
directions: Saute fiddleheads in butter in a heavy bottomed saute pan over moderate heat, stirring with wooden spoon for 2 or 3 minutes, being careful not to brown.
Pour Chardonnay wine into saute pan and cover immediately, allowing fiddleheads to steam until slightly wilted.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with crumbled bacon and serve at once.
Yields 2 servings.

title: beef steak stroganoff
directions: Brown meat; add onion.
Add liquid with dissolved bouillon cubes.
Cover; cook 2 hours.
Add mushrooms and sour cream. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: harvest gold salad
directions: Dissolve jello, cheese and marshmallows in boiling water.
Let set until partially thick.
Add pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Mix well and fold in Cool Whip.
Makes 8 x 8-inch pan.
Double recipe for 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: festive cheese logs
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature and the butter or margarine. Beat in small bowl until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients except nuts or seeds. Chill 2 hours or until firm. Divide mixture into 2 equal parts; shape into logs. Roll in chopped nuts or seeds. Wrap in plastic wrap securely and store in refrigerator.

title: keepsake brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water or very low heat. Remove from heat. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in walnuts.

title: cake with pineapple
directions: Cream sugar and eggs, then add rest of ingredients.
You don't have to use a mixer.
Bake in sheet cake pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato apple salad
directions: In a large bowl, gently toss first six ingredients.
Combine whipped topping and mayonnaise; fold into fruit mixture.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Makes 32 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat large pot of water to boiling.
Add pasta and cook to desired consistency.
Meanwhile, heat olive oil in medium skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and cook 30 seconds.
Add asparagus; cover and cook 3 minutes.
Add squash and mushrooms; cook 4 to 5 minutes longer until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat; stir in tomatoes and 1/2 cup boiling water from pasta pot.
Drain water from pasta and return pasta to pot.
Add sauce and toss to coat.
Season with pepper.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: quick onion rice
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine soup mix and water.
Over medium-high heat, heat to boiling. Stir in rice.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Brown floured steak in oil.
Place onions under steak.
Spoon mushroom soup over steak and add water.
Place potatoes and carrots on top and bake or cook in electric skillet for 2 hours at low heat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Layer these ingredients with cheese on top. Do not stir. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add egg; beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and soda and add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Drop by heaping teaspoons 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with fork tines.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes, or until set and slightly brown.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: caramel layer squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine in heavy saucepan first 2 ingredients.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until caramels are melted.
Keep warm. Combine in large bowl remaining ingredients except chocolate chips.
By hand stir until dough holds together.
Press 1/2 dough into pan.
Bake for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and caramel mixture over cooked dough.
Then sprinkle rest of dough over that.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: breadsticks
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt shortening in scalded milk; cool to lukewarm and add to yeast.
Sift flour, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Make well in center; add all liquid at once and beat until dough comes away from sides of bowl.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Marinate chicken with 1 teaspoon soy sauce and 1 teaspoon cornstarch.
Remove all bone and skin from chicken breast.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Marinate for 10 minutes.

title: thunder and lightning
directions: Mix together and eat. Amounts can be adjusted up or down. Amounts of sugar, salt and vinegar can be adjusted to taste if you like.

title: bean catcher fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces into buttermilk and then into a mixture of flour, salt, pepper, paprika, thyme and minced onion.
Melt butter in shallow baking pan in 400° oven.
Remove pan and place chicken in pan, turning to coat with butter.
Bake in single layer, skin side down, for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 30 more minutes.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cup up chicken and
put in pan with 3 1/2 quarts water, add onion, celery,
1 tablespoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and stew until tender,
remove
the
chicken,
but meat, return to broth with
corn.
Make
rivels
by combining 1 1/2 cups flour and a little salt and 1 beaten egg.
Mix together with fingers to form crumbs.
Add
then to broth and boil 15 minutes more. Drop in
the chopped hard-boiled eggs and parsley.
Soup must be
cooled thoroughly to avoid smothering.
Stir occasionally while
cooking in
refrigerator.
Do not cover.
If freezing, cool soup thoroughly before freezing.

title: crock-pot barbecued beef stew
directions: In skillet brown meat in oil; drain off fat.
Place onion rings, green pepper and garlic in slow cooker.
Place meat on top and sprinkle with salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add beef broth, undrained tomatoes, mushrooms and barbecue sauce; stir to mix. Cover and cook on low heat setting for 8 hours.
Turn cooker on high heat setting.
Blend 1/4 cup cold water slowly into cornstarch; stir into stew.
Cover and cook until thickened and bubbly, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stir and bake rolls
directions: Pour water in mixing bowl.
Add yeast and sugar.
Stir well. Add egg and oil, then stir in flour.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes, then cover and store in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, stir dough.
Half fill greased muffin pans.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Keeps well in refrigerator for one week.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: I use chicken breasts (about 3), boiled and diced.
I use the Pet pie shells in square box.
Use deep pie plate.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in shell.
Top with pie shell, then put egg white on top of shell.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: graham cracker fluff
directions: Soak gelatin
in
water.
Mix together sugar, milk, egg yolks and pinch of salt.	Boil 1 minute and add soaked gelatin and vanilla.
Set in
a
cool place to thicken but not harden. Then add egg
whites
and
cream.
Mix altogether with gelatin mixture.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together with mixer the first 4 ingredients. Then fold in the Cool Whip. Pour into crust. Then freeze for 4 hours or until firm.

title: play dough
directions: In large bowl mix together flour, salt and oil.
Add enough water to make a good consistency, about 1 to 1 1/2 cups.
Add food coloring.

title: green bean baskin
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add flour, milk, Velveeta, Tabasco, soy sauce, black pepper and Accent.
Cook until smooth.
Add mushrooms and water chestnuts (save small amount of chestnuts to put on top. Pour green beans in baking dish.
Pour sauce over beans.
Place the rest of water chestnuts on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion, garlic, green pepper and mushrooms until onions are transparent.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder and beans.
Heat through.
Stir yogurt and cottage cheese together.
In a 1 1/2-quart nonstick casserole, put a layer of sauce.
Top with yogurt mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot. Serves 8.

title: butterscotch rolls
directions: Grease a Bundt pan and sprinkle 1/3 of the nuts on the bottom of the pan.
Place rolls in bottom of pan and sprinkle with 1/3 more nuts.
Add pudding mix on top of rolls.
Melt butter and add brown sugar, pour over rolls and sprinkle remaining nuts.
Place in cold oven overnight.
In the morning, bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: breadsticks
directions: Mix well butter and dressing mix.
Cut each bun lengthwise into 8 sticks.
Spread sauce on bun sticks with pastry brush and bake for 4 hours at 200°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until knife inserted is clear.

title: kris kringle punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice, apple juice, lemon juice and orange juice in a punch bowl.
Just before serving, pour in ginger ale. Stir well.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Cream
cheese, mayonnaise and juice.
Add drained fruit, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Take American and Cheddar cheeses and grate.
Let cream cheese stand at room temperature.
Then mix with mayonnaise, mustard, garlic, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Roll into ball. Refrigerate.
Can cover with nuts, if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: three step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Pour into pie crust.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into loaf and bake at 350° in a shallow, rectangular baking dish for 1 hour.

title: marianne's chicken chutney salad
directions: Toss first 5 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and chill.
Mix together before serving.
Makes 5 large servings.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Take out 5 hours before serving. Chop up with a fork. Add ginger ale and 7-Up.

title: seafoam molded salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
Pour mix into a medium mixing bowl.
(A metal one is best and speeds the chilling process.)
Place Jell-O in the refrigerator until it becomes thickened, but not completely set.

title: shrimp stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds.
Cook peppers in boiling water 5 minutes; drain and set aside.
Saute onion and celery in margarine in a heavy saucepan until crisp-tender.
Add mushrooms and continue cooking until all vegetables are tender. Stir in chopped shrimp and cook 5 minutes or until done.
Add rice, salt and pepper to shrimp mixture, mixing well.
Stuff peppers with rice mixture.
Place peppers in an 8-inch square pan (baking dish). Pour 1/2 cup water into the dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Garnish with cooked shrimp and lemon wedges if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: low-fat chicken nuggets
