directions: Mix egg whites and spices in a small bowl. Combine baking mix and oat bran in a shallow pan. Cut chicken into small chunks.
Dip into egg mixture, then roll in baking mix and oat bran to coat. Place on cookie sheet coated with pan spray.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 30 minutes.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, cream cheese, salt and Cheez Whiz in a bowl. Saute onion in butter in skillet until brown.
Layer noodles, potatoes and onion mixture alternately in a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish until all ingredients are used, ending with onion mixture. Bake, covered, at 300°
for 20 minutes.
Uncover.
Broil until brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, squeeze out water, then mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, milk, cocoa and butter.
Boil 4 to 7 minutes or until thick.
Add peanuts butter and vanilla; stir. Pour over oatmeal in large bowl; mix well to coat oatmeal.
Put into greased pan to set.
When set, cut.

title: choco-nut meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Grease baking sheets; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl at high speed, beat the egg whites, vanilla, cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form.
Add sugar and, if desired, a few drops of food color.
Beat until very stiff and glossy and sugar is almost dissolved.
By hand, fold in pecans and chips.
Drop by well rounded teaspoonfuls about 1 inch apart onto baking sheets.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until set and dry to the touch.
Cool cookies on baking sheets for 1 minute.
Carefully transfer cookies to wire racks to cool.
Store loosely covered. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: garden fresh salsa
directions: Chop all of the vegetables separately into small pieces or use food chopper.
Mix together and add remaining ingredients.
If desired, add drops of hot sauce.

title: bread machine angel biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients in bread machine in order suggested by manufacturer.
Place on dough cycle.
When dough cycle is complete, remove dough and roll about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch rounds and place in lightly greased pan.
Allow to rise about 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
(Makes good raisin scones.)

title: mounds candy balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
In double boiler, melt paraffin wax and chocolate chips.
Place coconut mixture in freezer to harden to make handling easier.
Take out of freezer; roll into small balls, a few at a time.
Place mixture back in freezer.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on wax paper.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease loaf pan well and line bottom with wax paper. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Mix in chips, nuts, dates and cherries until well coated with flour. In a large bowl, beat eggs well on medium speed; gradually add sugar. Fold into flour mixture; turn into pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick onion soup
directions: Brown onions in butter until tender. Add bouillon and seasonings.
Cook until onions are tender.
Place slice of French bread in a bowl.
Pour soup over it.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Can be heated until cheese melts.

title: corn chowder
directions: Slice sausage into 1/4-inch thick slices.
In a dutch oven, combine sausage, corn, potatoes, onion, water, bouillon, and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes until corn and potatoes are just tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in 3 c. of the milk and the margarine.
Combine remaining milk and the flour.
Stir milk-flour mixture into the corn mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
*If using creamed corn, add creamed corn just before stirring in the milk.
Makes 6 main servings.

title: soft sugar cookie
directions: In large bowl mix together butter, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk; set aside.
Mix together sugar, salt, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Combine the dry ingredients slowly to the wet ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with granulated sugar (at Christmastime use red and green granulated sugar, be careful not to get sugar onto baking pan, sugar will burn).
Bake at 350° for 4 to 5 minutes or until done (top of cookie will spring back when touched).

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix molasses, brown sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, mix well.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or up to 1 week.
Bake at 325° until bread starts to brown around edges.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet until set, about 1 minute.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: choco-dot chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix 1/2 cup
brown
sugar,
Crisco,
milk, flour and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Press into pan and bake 10 minutes.

title: strawberry dream pie
directions: Combine vanilla pudding, strawberry jello, water and lemon juice in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Pour into bowl and chill until thickened.
To hasten chilling, place bowl of pudding mixture in large bowl of ice and water; stir until thickened.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Batter:
Mix in large bowl the eggs, milk and brown sugar; stir until blended.
In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Then, blend the two mixtures together.
Heat oil, preferably in an electric skillet, to 360°.
Using a funnel, pour 1/2 cup of batter into hot oil in a round zig-zag pattern.
Cook about 2 1/2 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to a plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 5 to 6 cakes.

title: mixed pickle
directions: Peel cucumbers and cut into chunks.
Mix with salt.
Cover with water.
Let stand 2 hours, drain.
Cook remaining ingredients in large pan.
Add cucumbers and cook until tender. Pack in hot jars and seal.
Process in hot water 10 minutes. Yields 4 pints.

title: golden potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine milk, shortening and potatoes; cook and stir over low heat just until shortening is melted.
Remove from heat and place in a large bowl with sugar, salt, 2 cups of flour and the yeast mixture. Add eggs; mix well.
Cover loosely and allow to stand for 2 hours (dough will be like a sponge).
Stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down and divide into thirds.
Form into rolls and place onto greased sheets.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Chop squash, pepper and onion and simmer 10 minutes; drain. Add mayonnaise, grated cheese and chilies, then add egg and pimentos.
Mix all together and put in buttered casserole. Sprinkle top with cracker or bread crumbs and drizzle with butter on top.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: yellow crookneck squash puff casserole
directions: Slice squash; cook in small amount of water until tender. Drain; mash.
Mix all ingredients except egg whites.
Fold in beaten egg whites lightly.
Turn into baking dish.
Set dish in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until set.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Mix well and let stand for 1 hour or overnight.
Beat eggs into mixture and add nuts, cinnamon, flour and baking powder.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan lightly.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Peel and clean cucumbers.
Grate on big side of cheese grater. Mix in other ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Refrigerate.
Use as dressing or a dip.

title: big dutch baby
directions: This is ideal for Sunday morning breakfast.

title: mimosa
directions: This is a drink for that special brunch you are having.
Pour 1 shot glass of champagne into glass, fill rest of glass with orange juice.

title: cincinnati chili(student favorite)
directions: In large pot, stir together beef and water so that beef separates to very fine texture.
Mix in all remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
During the last hour, pan may be covered upon reaching desired consistency.
Remove bay leaves before serving.
Serve in bowls with spaghetti, red beans, chopped onions and grated cheese or any combination.
Chili can also be used to make delicious Coney Island hot dogs.

title: white fudge
directions: Melt butter and almond bark.
Mix cream cheese and pour into almond bark mixture.
Beat 7 to 10 minutes until glossy.
Add nuts and pour into buttered 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and croutons.
Spoon into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pork chop and rice bake
directions: Brown chops on both sides and season.
In 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, combine soup, water and wine.
Stir in uncooked rice, mushrooms and bouillon, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and thyme.
Top with pork chops and add onion rings.
Cover and bake at 375° for 60 minutes.

title: date roll candy
directions: Cook milk, sugar and syrup to soft ball stage. Add dates and nuts; cook 5 more minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from fire. Add vanilla and butter. Beat until creamy.
Spread on wet cloth. Let stand until cool; roll and cut in slices.

title: chicken spaghetti no. 2
directions: Prepare spaghetti by package directions.
Boil chicken breasts for 30 minutes or until done.
Cut chicken into small pieces. Drain spaghetti.
Add soups and tomatoes to spaghetti.
Add chicken to spaghetti.
Season with garlic and onion powders, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole and add Velveeta cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: seafood spaghetti pie
directions: While cooking spaghetti, in large mixing bowl, combine clams, shrimp, crabmeat, 1 cup spaghetti sauce, 2 ounces of cheese and eggs.
When spaghetti is cooked and drained, toss into mixing bowl with other ingredients.
Season with garlic and Italian seasoning to taste.
Place in 9-inch greased pie plate.
Cover with remaining sauce, sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: open dish apple pie
directions: Sift flour and salt
together.	Blend
in the margarine and cream cheese.
Line a 12 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: potato casserole
directions: Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water.
Add sugar, salt and shortening to milk.
Add yeast to the milk mixture.
Mix and add 3 cups of flour and stir well.
Add more flour until dough is not so sticky.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for 30 minutes.
Place dough on floured board and knead until dough is blended well. Roll out and make into rolls.
Place in greased pan.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until well browned on top.
Brush with butter.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, and uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts and separate into small pieces.
Mix all other ingredients with chicken and chill overnight.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Brown bacon until light golden brown; drain.
Beat eggs until foamy; add milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat by hand until smooth.
Stir in meats and cheese; blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes (freezes well).
Slice and heat in microwave about 15 seconds per slice.

title: summer punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, diluting the frozen juices in the ginger ale and pineapple juice.
Pour over the frozen strawberries. Makes approximately 6 quarts.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Heat the 2 sugars, just to boiling point and add peanut butter.
Stir in cereal.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt together the chips in double boiler, spread on top; cool and cut into small squares.

title: chicken and stove top dressing casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Layer cheese over chicken. Spread cream of chicken soup evenly over cheese.
In separate bowl, mix the flavor packet with the dressing.
Sprinkle the dry dressing and flavoring over casserole.
Spray top of dressing with butter several times while baking.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shells until golden brown. Cut strawberries into bite size pieces.
Mix water, sugar and cornstarch together. Bring to a thick boil. Remove from heat. Stir in jello.
Place strawberries into baked pie shell. Cover with glaze mixture. Allow pies to set 3 to 4 hours. Top with Cool Whip.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, arrange in layers.
Pat uncooked ground chuck in bottom of baking pan.
Sprinkle salt and pepper seasoning.
Pour cheddar cheese soup (undiluted) on top of this, then add cream of mushroom soup (undiluted) on this.
Sprinkle onion over all and top with Tater Tots.
Cover completely.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Melt butter; mix remaining ingredients with butter.
Cover potatoes and cook for 40 minutes at 350°.
Uncover potatoes and sprinkle paprika over potatoes.
Return to oven and bake until tender.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, then add sifted flour and baking powder.
Alternately with milk, add coconut; fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Ice when cool.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Cover and cook an additional 3 to 5 hours on high, stirring occasionally.
Freezes well.

title: taco bell peppers
directions: Cut off tops and insides of green peppers.
Parboil in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Brown the beef and onion; drain fat.
Add 1 cup spaghetti sauce, rice, taco seasoning, pepper and diced green pepper reserved from tops. Spoon meat mixture into pepper shell.
Pour remaining 2 cups spaghetti sauce over peppers.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes or until tops are brown.

title: cheese crisp("it's a snack")
directions: Take a flour tortilla and place on a paper plate.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Placed in microwave until cheese is melted. Take it out and eat.
You can roll it up or pull it apart to eat. You can also heat on cookie sheet in the oven.
We love them and always have them on hand.
Try it.

title: blueberry cheese pie
directions: Slice the bananas and layer in the two pie crusts.
Combine the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and whipped cream.
Mix together until smooth.
Divide evenly over the 2 pie crusts. Refrigerate overnight.
Spread can of pie filling on top.
Makes 2 pies.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed and then drain.
In separate saucepan, mix cream cheese and mushroom soup.
Heat until creamy.
Add 3/4 can French fried onions and spinach.
Mix all together and place in 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining onions.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: "un-fried" crunchy french fries
directions: Take the potatoes and cut for fries.
Dip them in egg whites. Then place them on a cookie sheet sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Spray the cooking spray over the top of the fries as well. Then sprinkle a little Cajun spice over the fries.
Bake until brown, stirring sometimes to brown evenly.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in baking pan.
Spread salsa over cream cheese.
Sprinkle cheese over salsa.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: bread in a coffee can
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in a large mixer bowl and blend in ginger and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Let stand in a warm place until mix is bubbly, about 15 minutes.

title: east texas hot water corn bread
directions: Bring water to a brisk boil.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 of water and mix thoroughly.
Add more water, if needed, for thick mixture.
Spoon and pat with hands.
Fry in very hot oil until brown.
Everyone loves hot water cornbread in Marshall.

title: play-doh
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar together.
Add water, vegetable oil and food coloring.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it gets stiff and pulls off side of pan.
Knead a few times.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate peanut bars
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in peanut butter and remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, cereal and chocolate pieces.
Press into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix and place in pan. Pat until smooth. Cut into squares.

title: ham balls
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Mix meat, eggs and milk.
Blend in crumbs.
Shape into balls and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, vinegar, water and mustard.
Pour over balls and bake in slow oven for 3 hours.

title: tex mex chili
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, brown beef, onions, chili powder and pepper until brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in flour.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in V-8 juice and heat to boiling, stirring often.
Reduce to low heat and stir in beans. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate almond pie
directions: In double boiler combine chocolate bar, marshmallows and milk. Melt and stir until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Cool.
Whip the cream; add vanilla.
Fold cooled chocolate mixture into whipped cream.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: orange blush
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve over ice cubes.
Makes a wonderful breakfast or lunch beverage.

title: sweet-sour chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken in a deep baking dish.
Sprinkle soup mix over chicken. Pour Russian dressing over soup mix and spoon apricot marmalade over the Russian dressing.
Cover with foil and bake 40 minutes in a 325° to 350° oven.
Remove foil cover and continue baking another 20 to 30 minutes.
Chicken makes own gravy. Prepare rice as directed. Serve chicken on warm serving platter with the rice and gravy on the side.

title: peanut butter kandy cake
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour onto a well-greased cookie sheet (11 x 15-inch).
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Spread 1 cup peanut butter over cake while still hot! When cake is cooled, top with frosting.

title: garden vegetable casserole
directions: Place all sliced vegetables in microwave container.
Mix all other ingredients.
Toss lightly with vegetables.
Cover and microwave on Full power for 8 to 10 minutes.
Conventional Oven: Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sister-in-law cheese ball
directions: Blend softened cheeses; add onion, sauce, 1/2 nuts and 1/2 parsley.
Shape into a ball and chill.
Roll ball in remaining nuts and parsley.
Great served with Wheatsworth crackers.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream margarine and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Gradually add to sugar, margarine and eggs.
You may wish to omit the salt from this recipe.

title: cheese rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and rice in margarine until rice is slightly brown, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Arrange layers of the rice mixture with the shredded cheese in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: oven baked chicken or pork chops
directions: Pat meat pieces day with paper towel.
Coat with dry ingredients.
Dip coated pieces into combined milk and egg. Recoat with dry.
Arrange pieces in shallow baking pan.
Do not touch each other.
Drizzle with peanut oil.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown (30 to 35 minutes for boneless meat).

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and margarine. Add eggs, pecans and vanilla flavoring. Pour into a pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer if needed.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Five minutes before cake is done, mix margarine, cocoa, milk and vanilla.
Put on stove.
Cook until butter melts.
Add sugar. Mix.
Spread on hot cake.
Add nuts, if you wish.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Combine with other ingredients. Simmer.
Serve on toasted buns.

title: dilly barbecued turkey
directions: Place turkey in a glass baking dish.
In a small bowl, combine all remaining ingredients; spread over the turkey.
Cover and refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Remove turkey; reserve marinade.

title: applesauce-raisin spice cake(diabetic)
directions: Cook raisins in water until soft.
Cool and drain.
Add to raisins, applesauce, eggs, sugar substitute and oil.
Mix well. Blend in soda, flour, spices, vanilla and salt.
Pour in a greased and floured Bundt pan or 24 cupcake pans with liners.
Bake cake at 350° for 50 minutes or bake cupcakes at 350° for 25 minutes. Makes 24 servings.	Contains 140 calories.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Cut onions and peppers and put on top of pork chops.
Add the tomato juice and simmer for about an hour or until onions and pepper are tender.
The tomato juice, onion and pepper mixture is good over boiled potatoes.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Mix together cocoa and water until smooth, let cool.
In a large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add shortening and cooled cocoa mixture.
Beat with a wooden spoon for 2 minutes.
Add 2 eggs, unbeaten, beat for 2 more minutes.
Fill paper muffin liners 1/2 full and bake for 20 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 16.

title: peppered hominy
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all the ingredients and put in glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: jan's grape pie
directions: Separate grape pulp from skins.
Cook pulp until you can strain out seeds.
Mix all ingredients and skins.
Put in pie shell with lattice top and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.
The grapes cook down.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and milk.
Pour evenly over butter.
Combine berries, sugar and water.
Spoon evenly over flour mixture; do not stir.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp stuffed eggs
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise; scoop out yolks.
Mash yolks thoroughly with a fork.
Beat in mayonnaise, mustard, dill and salt.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix sliced squash with melted butter and place in casserole. Combine the egg, mayonnaise, onion, pepper, pimento and sugar and spoon over squash.
Sprinkle grated cheese and cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pasta with cheese
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Add vegetables during the last 2 minutes of cooking.
Drain.
Gently toss in a large bowl with shredded cheeses, 2 1/2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and margarine.

title: christmas salad
directions: Toss lettuce, avocado, red onion, cranberries and mandarin oranges together. Mix cranberry juice concentrate, rice wine vinegar, mustard, pepper and oil. Pour over salad and toss.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup Colby in large bowl, mixing well.
Turn into 9 x 13-inch baking dish, buttered.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Top with remaining Colby.
Let melt over casserole.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Cream margarine and sugars.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Begin and end with flour mixture.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Fold into batter.
Pour into pan.
Bake 90 minutes or until done.
Let cake rest in pan 30 minutes before removing.

title: turketti spaghetti sauce
directions: Add oil to 2-quart saucepan or 10-inch skillet.
Set over low heat.
Add turkey, onion and green pepper and cook, breaking apart with spoon, until turkey is crumbly and no longer pink (about 10 minutes).
Stir in garlic, then tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper. Bring to a simmer and cook, covered, over lowest heat setting for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot, cooked spaghetti or linguine with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: best fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Slice bananas.
Put lemon juice over them.
Mix together and enjoy.

title: zucchini and pepper enchiladas
directions: In a large heavy skillet, saute the garlic and onion in olive oil with salt.
When the onions are soft, add the peppers, zucchini and herbs.
Stir and cook on medium heat for 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the cheese.
Cool to room temperature before filling enchiladas.
Prepare red enchilada sauce (next recipe).

title: banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs,
beat 1 minute.
Add bananas with the flour mixture. Beat only
until blended.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased loaf pan in
oven
and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: granny's filled cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream together shortening, granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into batter. Chill.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Mix together the sugar, vinegar, pepper, salt and celery seed. Pour over the prepared vegetables and mix well.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Place unfilled mushrooms, rounded side up, on baking sheet. Brush tops with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat, 2 to 3 minutes, until lightly browned.
Remove.

title: veggie squares
directions: Spread rolls on 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: banana-bran bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then bran. Combine water and bananas (in blender if possible).
Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and add vanilla and nuts.
Use a 5 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
I use these as muffins.
Makes 12 medium.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix together.
Shape into balls or patties (1-inch size). Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix the crushed graham crackers and 2/3 cup of melted margarine well.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: 2 chocolate pies
directions: Blend dry ingredients and add milk and water.
Stir constantly over medium heat.
After it thickens, add vanilla and butter.
Pour into cooked pie shells.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add soups and milk.
Mix well.
Add chicken and turn into a casserole dish. Saute almonds in 1/2 cup butter.
Add crumbs and mix well. Sprinkle on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apricot bars
directions: Line 9X13 pan with 15 squares of Graham crackers. Melt margarine in saucepan. Mix in together sugar and egg, and add milk. Cook together until slightly thick, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat, stir in graham cracker crumbs, coconut, nuts and apricots. Add vanilla.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage in water until done.
Drain, crumble and brown meat with the onion.
Add all of the dry ingredients and continue to brown until the onion is tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste and simmer until the sauce is hot and bubbly.
Cook 2 pounds of spaghetti and mix with sauce.

title: tuna casserole(microwave dish)
directions: Blend soup and milk in 2-quart micro-type casserole.
Add remaining ingredients, except chow mein noodles; blend well.
Use High cycle and cook 9 minutes.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Cook another 3 to 5 minutes.

title: muenster chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1 to 2-inch squares. Soak in beaten eggs for 45 minutes. Coat with bread crumbs and brown in margarine or oil. Place in single layer in baking dish.
Cover with mushrooms and add chicken broth.
Place cheese slices over all. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes, covered, and 10 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: texas barbecued beef
directions: *These
are
difficult to find in Tennessee, so I sometimes use a London Broil cut.

title: marinated turkey steaks
directions: Mix together in a big bowl and put cold, even a little bit frozen, turkey steak strips in the marinade.
(The turkey steaks are better if cut up in strips), then you marinate for about 3 to 4 hours.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and put into a greased baking dish.
Top with extra cheese, if desired, and bake 1 hour at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Combine soup and wine.
Put chicken breasts in dish; cover with cheese.
Top with soup and wine.
Cover with stuffing mix. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: golden turkey quiche
directions: Bake pie shell.
Cook celery in butter until tender.
Stir in turkey and pimento.
Beat together eggs, milk, mayonnaise, mustard and salt.
Stir in turkey mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: friendship
directions: Mix up slowly.
Keep forever in a good heart.
Remember to share with others.

title: cherry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beat eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla. Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Spread half of mixture in greased and floured pan.
Spread pie filling, then add rest of batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and flour to make paste.
Add egg and juice.
Whip.
Cook until thick.
Pour over all ingredients while hot.
Refrigerate.

title: hot mushroom dip
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until all liquid is absorbed.
Mix mushrooms, sour cream and soup mix.
Put mixture in an ovenproof serving dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake until bubbly, approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers or French bread.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes, then cook in slightly salted water. Cool and add other ingredients.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir shortening, brown sugar, salt, vanilla, white sugar and eggs all together well.
Mix the flour, oats and baking soda together; add to first mixture.
Add walnuts and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls and bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: creme brulee
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Adjust the rack to the center of the oven.

Place six 6-oz. ramekins in a larger baking pan, making sure the larger pan is at least 1/2 inch deeper than the ramekins. Bring the cream, 1/2 c. sugar, and the vanilla bean and scraped seeds to a simmer in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Remove from the heat, cover the pan with plastic film and let steep for 15 minutes.

title: striped salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello and chill (morning day before).
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add marshmallows to lemon jello and stir until melted.
Add pineapple juice and beat in cream cheese until blended real well.
Add drained pineapple and cool slightly.
Fold mayonnaise into whipped cream and add to jello mixture.
Pour onto lime jello previously prepared.
Now make cherry jello, cool slightly and pour over other jello.

title: saucy baked pork chops
directions: Brown the chops on both sides and season with the salt and pepper.
Place browned chops in a baking dish.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Pour over the chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tortilla appetizer wedges
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream; mix well.
Stir in chilies, onion, jalapenos, salt and pepper.
Spread 1 tortilla with about 1/4 cup of mixture; top with another tortilla.

title: pecan pie surprise bars
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, and pour on baked crust. Sprinkle pecans over top of filling.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese with sugar; spread over crust.
Cover with sliced strawberries.
Mix pudding with milk according to package directions.
Fold Cool Whip into pie filling and pour over strawberries.
May cover with extra Cool Whip.
Refrigerate (best if eaten same day).

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine egg and buttermilk; set aside.
Combine 1/4 cup all-purpose flour, cornmeal, 1 teaspoon salt, and pepper in shallow bowl or pan.
Dredge tomato slices in remaining 1/4 cup flour; dip in egg mixture, then dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Pour oil to a depth of 1/4-inch to 1/2-inch in a large cast-iron skillet; heat to 375°.
Drop tomatoes, in batches, into hot oil, and cook 2 minutes on each side or until golden.
Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle hot tomatoes with salt if desired.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Melt butter and cook onions a little.
Take all fat off of meat and wash it.
Brown meat in melted butter.
Add water, covering meat halfway.
Add soup mix, peppers and tomato sauce to water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook for about 3 hours. Keep pan covered and turn meat every 1/2 hour.
Serve with potatoes and carrots.

title: longevity minestrone
directions: Heat oil in a heavy bottom 4-quart pot.
Add garlic and onion; saute until soft and translucent.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon salt, carrots, celery, broccoli and spinach.
Add oregano, pepper and basil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 to 8 minutes.
Add green pepper, water, tomato puree and chickpeas (garbanzo beans). Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Simmer 10 minutes.
Then bring soup to a boil and add dry pasta. Boil about 10 minutes.
Ladle into bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place fryer in baking dish or pan.
Brush with margarine and A.1. sauce.
Sprinkle soup mix over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover the last few minutes of baking time.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Soften flour tortillas in 1/4 cup hot oil by frying about 3 seconds on each side.
Let these drain on paper towels.
Have your chicken deboned and chopped.
In medium saucepan, combine canned milk, cheese and soup.
Heat until cheese melts.
Take off burner and add green onion dip mix and green chilies.
Place chopped chicken in tortillas and roll, place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour soup mixture over tortillas.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in oats, walnuts and chips.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart. Flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in granulated sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spiced apples and sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and thinly slice the apples.
Peel and grate the sweet potatoes.
Pour apple juice concentrate into a stainless steel Dutch oven.
Add apples and sweet potatoes and cook over low flame until tender, but not mushy.
Stir in dates and raisins to heat through.
Add spices to taste.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Place all in a casserole.
Lightly toast almonds on a baking sheet under broiler.
Cover entire top of casserole with the nuts.

title: carolyn's cocktail sauce
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 5 ingredients together and pour over potatoes.
Melt butter and add crumbs; sprinkle crumb mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine lemon juice, oil, garlic and pepper. Arrange chicken in casserole or baking pan, pour lemon and oil mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° until tender, about 40 minutes, baste occasionally.
Uncover casserole and bake 10 minutes longer to brown chicken.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: camp potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and slice.
In large bowl toss potatoes, onions, peppers and squash.
Arrange 6 sheets of aluminum foil.
Place potato mixture in center of each sheet.
Dot with pats of margarine; sprinkle with cheese.
Seal foil around mixture.
Place foil in hot coals or on top of grill.
Cook approximately 40 minutes or until tender.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, vinegar, Wesson oil, salt and pepper to taste.
Remove from heat and cool.
Toss over well mixed vegetables and cool.

title: raisin upside-down cake
directions: Mix white sugar, flour, baking powder and salt all together. Stir in melted margarine, raisins, milk and eggs and mix well. Pour into greased pan.
Mix brown sugar and boiling water and pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: paper cup frozen salad
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, sugar, salt, drained pineapple, banana and food coloring.
Lightly fold in nuts and cherries.
Spoon into paper muffin cups, which have been placed in 3-inch muffin pans.
Cover with plastic wrap to freeze.
Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving.
Remove from paper cups and place on greens.

title: chicken parisian
directions: In plastic bag, combine flour, paprika and pepper.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time; shake to coat.
In skillet, brown chicken in margarine; remove from pan.

title: perfect popovers
directions: Grease pan with spray or shortening.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Spoon onto pan.
Preheat oven to 400°. Cook until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; put dill in bottom of each jar.
Place cucumbers neatly in jar.
Bring vinegar mixture to boil.
Pour over cucumbers. Add alum. Put on lids.
Set aside to cure for 6 weeks.
Mixture can be saved to use for next batch.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in large pan and bake at 350° for an hour or bake at lower temperature for a longer time.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Marinate the eggplant in salt water, rinse and drain.
Cook eggplant in a mixture of Sauterne, water, Worcestershire, hot sauce and soy sauce until it can be mashed.
Pour into a colander, saving the juice.

title: bavarian bread dumplings(great with sauerbraten)
directions: Cut bread into small pieces and put in bowl and sprinkle with salt.
Pour milk over bread and soak about 1 hour.
Pour off excess milk, if there is any.

title: bierox
directions: Prepare bread dough; let rise.
In large saucepan, combine shortening, cabbage, onion, salt and pepper; cook down.
Brown hamburger in skillet; drain.
Combine with cabbage mixture.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Chop cookies in blender (finely crushed).
By hand, blend margarine and Oreos.
Set aside.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat water, shortening and salt to boiling point.
Add flour all at once.
Stir vigorously until mixture leaves sides of pan and clings to the spoon.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly, then add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Turn off heat and leave puffs in oven until they are dry (about 20 minutes).
Makes about 16 medium puffs.
Cut puffs open and fill with pudding.

title: cherry nut fudge
directions: Bring sugar, cream and dash of salt to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add the salt.
Cook until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; let stand until almost cold.
Beat mixture until thick and creamy.
Cover with a damp cloth; let stand 30 minutes.
Add vanilla, nuts and cherries; work in with hands.
Press into a shallow, waxed paper lined pan. Makes 1 pound.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Bring butter, sugar, syrup, salt, baking powder and vanilla to boil, stirring constantly.
Then boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Turn into baking pan and put in 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes while baking.
Break apart and store in tins.

title: broccoli-n-pasta
directions: Steam broccoli according to package.
Heat oil and saute onion, parsley and garlic until onion is tender.
Stir in broccoli.
Take off heat, put into bowl and add all other ingredients; stir and serve.
Serves 6.

title: rum cake
directions: Put nuts on bottom of Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Mix cake mix, instant pudding, eggs, oil, water and rum.
Pour over nuts in the cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: greece a roni
directions: Fry bacon.
Leave grease in pan.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Pour in noodles and cook until done.
Drain noodles and add cheese.
Have a great meal!

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Catch some Laguna Madre Trout.
Filet 'em and try this recipe!

title: italian cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Add the flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Combine pretzels, butter and sugar and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together and spread over first layer. Refrigerate.
Mix jello and boiling water until dissolved.
Add strawberries and pour over top.

title: yellow split pea soup
directions: Bring first 9 ingredients to a boil and simmer 45 minutes. Adjust salt and add cumin, turmeric and curry.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: rice with mushrooms
directions: Put everything in oven proof casserole dish.
Put in preheated oven at 350° and bake 1 hour.
Double for company - MMM good.

title: lemon lush
directions: Layer 1:
Mix magarine, flour and pecans together like pie dough.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool slightly and while still warm, mix and spread on Layer 2.

title: crappie delite
directions: Heat soybean oil to 400 degrees. Blend all ingredients except fish together to create a batter.
Dip fillets into batter and fry until golden brown.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Combine the beef and onion in a heavy skillet.
Cook until beef browns.
Drain excess grease. Add catsup, mustard, and milk. Stir and continue cooking for about 1 to 2 minutes.
Taste and add salt only if needed.
Spoon onto buns.
Makes about 6 to 8 spoon burgers.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix together pineapple, cheese, sugar and flour.
Put crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Drizzle melted butter over top of crackers and put in oven for 30 - 35 minutes. Serve hot or cold.
You can also add coconut and chopped maraschino cherries to this dish.

title: spice pecans
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 pan, then mix all spices with butter. Add pecans and stir well.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes stirring at least once.

title: skillet upside-down pineapple cake
directions: Preheat skillet to 250°.
Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar until all melted and mixed.
Pineapple juice can be used for some of the water in cake mix.
Pour mix over sugar mixture and spread evenly.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes with lid on.
With a spatula, loosen sides of cake.
Place on wire rack to cool.
Serve plain or with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: frosted apple-raisin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine apples, raisins, sugars, flour, cinnamon and lemon rind in mixing bowl.
Arrange in closely packed layers in a 9-inch pastry lined pie plate.
Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
Dot with butter.
Place top crust over filling. Fold edge under bottom crust, pressing to seal.
Flute to make standing edge.
Cut slits for steam to escape.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar.
Add 1/2 of flour and 1 cup of buttermilk and mix well.
Add other half of flour.
Mix well. Add soda to the other cup of buttermilk and beat well.
Add beaten eggs and flour.
Cook at 250° or 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: spinach in a bread bowl
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread.
Cut circle in top of one loaf of bread.
Hollow it out.
Put filling inside.
Cut remaining loaf into cubes.
Serve with small knife to spread filling on cubes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix and fry in butter.

title: crispy baked fish fillets
directions: Melt the butter and pour into a shallow bowl.
Add the paprika and lemon pepper.
Crush the crackers and the potato chips.
Mix them together in a small bowl and pour the crumbs onto a plate or waxed paper.
Dip the fish fillets in the butter mixture and coat with the crumbs.
Place the fillets in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes for small fillets and 10 minutes for large.
Turn the oven to broil and cook the fish for 5 to 7 minutes or until nicely browned.
Serves 4.

title: buttery microwave potatoes
directions: In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, melt butter on High for 50 to 60 seconds.
Stir in seasoned salt and pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients until coated with butter.
Cover.
Cook until potatoes are fork-tender, 13 to 15 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Yields eight 1/2-cup servings.

title: diet orange fluff
directions: Mix cheese, oranges, pineapple and dry Jell-O together with Cool Whip.
(Make sure the pineapple and oranges are drained before adding to mixture.)
Serves great as a snack with crackers!

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Pour in a square dish and refrigerate until congealed.
Very good! Very pretty!
Great for Christmas!

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Start to cook noodles.
In a large skillet, cook onion and garlic in oil for 2 minutes.
Slice steak thinly and add to onion and garlic.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup; cook until creamy.
Add sour cream.
Stir for 1 minute or until mixed well.
Add cooked noodles and pepper to taste.
Serve with rolls and salad.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt the butter with the brown sugar.
Place sliced pineapple in brown sugar mixture.
Place cherries in center of pineapple slices.
Make batter of flour, baking powder, white sugar, pineapple juice and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add to batter.
Pour the batter over the pineapple slices and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.	Cut in shortening.
Mix water, egg and vinegar.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix.
Can be kept in refrigerator two weeks.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cut stew hen into serving pieces.
Place in large kettle with next 5 ingredients.
Cover with 2 quarts of water and bring to boil.
After liquid has come to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until hen is tender.
(Add salt after cooking about an hour.) Remove chicken from broth, cool, and cut into bite size pieces. Strain broth and discard vegetables.
Skim all fat from chicken broth.
Bring 1 1/2 quarts broth to a boil, add noodles and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add chicken.
Add pepper and more salt, if needed.

title: grape nut pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Grape-Nuts on bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture on top and sprinkle 1/2 cup Grape-Nuts on top.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Place 10 x 13-inch pan in larger pan with water.

title: eggs de vaughan
directions: Butter bread, both sides, and cut into cubes.
Combine milk, eggs and seasonings.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer bread and cheese, ending with cheese.
Pour egg mixture over layers.
Let stand overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Wash, drain and slice strawberries.
Combine jello, pudding mix and water in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over high heat to a full boil and remove from heat.
Add strawberries and let stand 5 minutes.
Pour into a cooled pie shell and refrigerate 4 hours. Serve with whipped cream.

title: mochamallow
directions: Combine coffee, cocoa and cinnamon or vanilla in blender and blend on high until smooth.
Add hot milk and blend until foamy. Pour into preheated mugs and top with marshmallows.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: flower pot surprise dessert
directions: Put cookies in blender to crumble. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar well. Add dry pudding and milk; mix well.
Stir in Cool Whip well. Alternate pudding and crumbs, ending with crumbs. You can use any container which is not see through. Skim milk and sugar free pudding can be used.
One half batch fills 12 (7 ounce) styrofoam cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in the margarine.
Combine remaining ingredients and bake in a casserole dish for 1 hour at 325°.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Mix together bread crumbs, Romano cheese, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper by rubbing in hands.
Cut tops and bottom from artichoke and turn upside down.
Mash lightly to open leaves. Fill each leaf from outside in by using the top of each leaf.
Pour oil over stuffed piece.
Steam in covered pot in a little water 45 minutes or longer. Done when leaf pulls off easily.

title: squash bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients except sugar.
Beat eggs.
Add oil and vanilla.
Stir in squash; mix with dry ingredients.
Gradually stir in sugar.
Pour into a bread pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Defrost; drain spinach.
Beat eggs; add cottage cheese, flour, salt and grated cheese.
Stir together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tuna noodle
directions: Mix all the
ingredients (except noodles) in a saucepan over medium heat
until
cheese
is melted and all ingredients are well mixed.
In
a second pot, cook noodles as directed on package. When done,
drain
noodles
and
combine
with other ingredients. Mix well.
May
serve
as
is or bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs, if desired.

title: lemon pudding dessert
directions: This recipe is done in layers.
The first layer is the crust. Mix flour, margarine and some chopped walnuts as you would for regular pie crust until the size of small peas.
Pat this mixture into 13 x 9-inch dish and bake at 300° for 30 minutes; let crust cool.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, then bake at 350° for 2 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix Marshmallow Creme and strawberry cream cheese together and it's ready to serve.
Serve with bananas, grapes, cantaloupe and strawberries.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix graham cracker crumbs with butter.
Add each item to butter and crackers in order given. Drizzle on milk, but do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine celery, chicken or turkey, mayonnaise, almonds (if using), cheese, lemon juice, salt and pepper in a large bowl; mix well.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crushed chips.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crustless pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray large pan or several pie pans. Combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Pour in pan or pie pans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix
pudding,
milk,
sour cream, Cool Whip and vanilla until smooth.
Layer
this
with a box of vanilla wafers and 8 bananas. Yields 10 servings.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Place cucumbers
in
stone
or	glass
jar.
Cover with boiling water.
Let
stand	24
hours.
Drain
off water.
Cut cucumbers in
desired pieces.
Add alum and cover with boiling water.
Let
stand 24 hours.
Rinse in clear water; drain off. Boil vinegar, sugar (6 cups) and spices tied up in cheesecloth and pour
over	cucumbers.
Boil
mornings, adding 1 cup of sugar each
morning,
then
boil 3 mornings without adding any sugar. Last, can in sterilized jars and lids.
Seal.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream
butter,
Crisco and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, about 1/3 at a
time.
Add
vanilla.
Add
eggs,
one at a time, beating constantly.
Pour
into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour
and 25 minutes at 300°.
Empty cake onto plate promptly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate lover's dream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Generously grease 12-cup Bundt pan with shortening; lightly flour. Mix cake mix, chocolate milk, butter, eggs, sour cream and pudding mix (dry) in large bowl with spoon until blended (batter will be very thick). Stir in chocolate chips. Spoon into pan.

title: oatmeal (raisin) cookies
directions: To plump raisins, cover with very hot water.
Soak 2 to 5 minutes.
Drain well before using.

title: easy tea cakes
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla. Mix together well.
Add flour a little at a time until you have worked all the flour in.
Chill for 1 hour.
Then flour surface and roll out.
Remember to keep both sides of dough floured.
Cut out and bake.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until lightly browned.
Best if you frost cookies while they are hot. Use a thin glaze.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat the eggs on high speed of mixer for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in the sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir in together the remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Spread in a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with the chopped pecans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Start rolling at narrow end.
Roll towel and cake together.
Cool; unroll.
Spread with filling and reroll cake.

title: guacamole
directions: With a large spoon, scoop pulp from skin of avocados into a bowl.
Mash avocados with potato masher, leaving slightly chunky; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fold into avocados gently, not to mush.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve as dip with tortilla chips.
Yields 4 cups.

title: broiled scallops
directions: Coat scallops with melted butter and fresh lemon juice.
Place on foil wrapped broiler pan.
Sprinkle with fine bread crumbs, a dash of garlic powder and a little salt and pepper.
Then a sprinkling of dry vermouth and under the broiler for 5 to 6 minutes.
A small amount works well in toaster oven.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone. Save broth to cook noodles in.

Saute chopped onion and pepper in 1/2 butter. Put cheese, tomatoes, salt and pepper into cooked and drained noodles while hot; mix well to melt. Add chicken, put in casserole and put rest of butter in slices on top. Bake at 350° until butter melts.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together
white sugar, cocoa, milk and butter. Bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal; mix well.
Drop on wax paper with teaspoons.
Let cool.

title: glazed shallots with port wine
directions: Melt butter in a frypan over medium-high heat.
Add shallots, pepper and salt.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Blend slowly all ingredients except eggs.
Blend in eggs one at a time on low speed.

title: southern peanut pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, syrup, butter, salt and vanilla.
Continue to beat until thoroughly blended.
Stir in peanuts.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
May be garnished with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frosted dill pickles
directions: Using medium size pickle, frost with cream cheese.
Roll in chopped dried beef and chill until firm.
Cut crosswise and serve with toothpick.

title: christmas essence
directions: Chop peels of orange and lemon.
Mix with cinnamon pieces, cloves and bay leaves.
Simmer mixture in 2 1/2 cups water.
It will create a spicy scent throughout the house.
May be used several times.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, oil and eggs with mixer.
By hand add dry ingredients, gradually.
Make small balls by hand and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press out with glass or cup that has been dipped in water.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: peach pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour and oleo together.
Then add the diced peaches and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fudge squares
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Melt chocolate and butter.
Mix in sugar, eggs, Bisquick and nuts.
Spread in 8-inch or 9-inch greased square pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat.
Remove from heat, gradually add in milk, cornstarch, sugar, coconut and salt.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Bake cake, remove from pan and leave out, uncovered, overnight (to dry it a little).
Divide ingredients in 2 parts.
In a 5-quart container or baking dish, layer broken pieces of cake, Kahlua, pudding, Heath bar crunch and Cool Whip and repeat.
Garnish top with some leftover Heath bar crunch.

title: bacon cheese treats
directions: Grind raw onion, bacon and cheese together.
Refrigerate covered for two hours or until ready to serve.
Spread on party rye.
Broil 2 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot.
Yields 2 loaves of party rye.
This may be frozen.

title: texas gravel(party mix)
directions: Place in a large roasting pan the first 6 ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Blend into cream mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll each ball in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chuck wagon carrots
directions: Bring 1 cup water to a boil in a 2-quart saucepan and add carrots.
Cover and cook over medium heat until carrots are tender-crisp, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
In same saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in carrots and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Yield: 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: wilted cabbage salad
directions: Fry bacon in skillet; remove bacon and add chopped cabbage to drippings.
Cook until wilted down (about 5 minutes).
Add chopped tomatoes, onion, celery and green pepper.
Stir into cabbage and add two to three tablespoons vinegar.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cook about 5 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well; add bread crumbs until stiff.
Put in pan; pour remaining tomato sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: raspberry cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped almonds.
Cut in shortening until fine crumbs.
Set aside 1/2 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Press the rest in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and almond extract until smooth.
Spread over hot crust.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes.
Spread preserves over cream cheese mixture.
Mix reserved crumbs, coconut and sliced almonds.
Sprinkle over preserves.
Bake 15 minutes more. Cool in pan on rack.
Chill 3 hours.
Cut in bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cherry and peach dumplings
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients into a 10-inch pan.
Heat and add peaches; bring to a boil.
Mix egg and water mix to Bisquick.
Stir into a soft dough.
Drop by teaspoons on top of boiling fruit. Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Stir softly.
Cover and cook 10 more minutes.
Serve warm with or without whipped topping.
Serves 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients above and pour into a deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour or until set.

title: luba's broccoli cheese potato soup
directions: In large pot, place peeled and diced potatoes, minced onion, garlic and onion powder and chicken seasoning.
Add enough water to just cover potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are soft, then mash. While potatoes are cooking, cook and coarsely chop broccoli.
Add broccoli, milk, Velveeta and butter to mashed potato mixture. Heat until cheese is melted and serve.
If soup is too thick, add more milk.
If soup is too thin, add instant potato flakes.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and cream alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.
Grease and flour pans.

title: orange slice balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except sugar).
Prepare a shallow pan with a brown paper bag liner.
Grease paper bag with Pam.
Put mixture in pan and bake for 25 minutes at 300°.
Cool. Spoon by the tablespoons and form balls.
Roll balls in confectioners sugar. Place on wax paper.

title: oysters rockefeller casserole
directions: Drain oysters.
Melt butter and saute celery.
Add onion, parsley, spinach, anise seed, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Add bread crumbs.
Spray a shallow casserole dish.
Arrange oysters in single layer only. Cover with Rockefeller mixture evenly.
Bake in 400° oven approximately 20 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle evenly with Parmesan.
Return to oven and broil for a minute or two until brown.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients together.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with the Dream Whip, prepared according to directions.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare sauce.
Melt butter in saucepan. Blend in flour.
Stir in milk and seasonings.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and add 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Alternate layers of macaroni and sauce in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: hamburger macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Brown ground beef and onion with crushed garlic.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in Sloppy Joe mix to ground beef; mix thoroughly.
Mix in tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and bay leaf; salt to taste.
Let simmer for 1/2 hour.
Boil macaroni; drain.
Stir in macaroni with beef mixture and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer top with cheese (cut into triangle shape).
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until cheese is melted.

title: deer meat chili
directions: Mix all together; cook and enjoy.

title: pork medallions
directions: Flatten slices with the heel of your hand.
Spread medallions on one side with mustard.
Saute in butter (mustard side first) for 5 minutes on each side.
Remove to warm platter.
Add beef broth and tarragon to pan and scrape up the drippings.
Simmer until half the liquid is gone.
Add half and half.
Simmer until thick.
Pour over meat and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fritter fried okra
directions: Sift dry
ingredients
together.
Combine eggs and milk and add to
dry
ingredients,
stirring until smooth.
Fold in okra. Spoon into hot, deep fat and fry until crisp.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pineapple and juice with the jello.
Bring to a boil. Stir to dissolve the jello.
Set aside to cool.
Mix buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Add cooled pineapple mixture and refrigerate. Serves 8.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. On stove top, mix ground beef, seasoning, onion and

tomatoes. Cook thoroughly. In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, line bottom with Cheddar cheese. Pour in beef mixture and spread evenly. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top. Bake at 350° until golden brown (about 45 minutes).

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spread on a flat plate.
Spread chili sauce.
Top with flaked crabmeat.
Refrigerate.
Let stand about 1/2 day.
Cover with chopped parsley.
One hour or so before serving, take out of refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt together sugar, margarine and cocoa.
Let cool.
Add to cooled mixture: eggs one at a time, all-purpose flour, salt, pecans and vanilla.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
While hot cover cake with marshmallows.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients together and form into a ball.
Roll ball in chili powder.
Cover with Saran Wrap and chill.

title: "butch's baked beans"
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and pepper and drain.
Place pork and beans in large mixing bowl and add brown sugar.
Add cooked hamburger, onion and pepper.
Squirt ketchup on top and stir to make soupy.
Pour into baking pan and cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly.

title: gail's fudge
directions: Melt bits over very low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Put mixture in well buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Toast pecans in shallow pan in oven at 250° for a few minutes. Check often.
Melt chocolate in microwave bowl.
Pour pecans in and stir to be well coated with chocolate.
Drop clusters with teaspoon on wax paper (store well).

title: salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple together. Bring to a simmer.
Set aside; let cool.
Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese with Jell-O. Chill.

title: great grammom willey's most asked for pound cake
directions: Put all in bowl at one time.
Blend slowly for one minute. Then beat at medium speed for 20 minutes.
(Good time to clean up.)
Do not put in preheated oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured large tube pan.
Ingredients can be cut in half, as this makes a large cake.
Drizzle white icing over cake.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, creaming after each.
Add sour cream and flour (sift flour and soda together before adding to mixture).
Add vanilla.
Cream well and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done. Cool 10 minutes in pan.
(May need to increase temperature a little last 15
minutes.)

title: baked macaroni and ham
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in a medium bowl.
Mix in baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into a ball on surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with 2 inch biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Let rise in warm place about 30 minutes or until soft and puffed.
Heat oven to 425° and bake 6 to 8 minutes or until browned.
Makes 9 to 11 buns.

title: quick fried rice
directions: Cook rice (omit salt and butter).
In frypan, heat olive oil and garlic.
Saute onions.
Add rice and soy sauce; mix well. Pour egg over rice and cook egg.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips with 14 ounces almond bark in large saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries; sprinkle with coconut.
Melt remaining 2 ounces almond bark with oil over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over coconut.
Chill until firm.
Store at room temperature.
Preparation time: 15 minutes plus chilling.

title: applesauce puffs
directions: Mix Bisquick, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan and dip in 2 tablespoons melted butter, then 1 1/4 sugar with 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Yields 12 delicious muffins.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet and drain.
Add all ingredients except the flour.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring often.
Add flour and simmer 1 more hour, stirring often.

title: lamb and cauliflower
directions: Boil lamb, chopped onions, cumin, salt, pepper and water until meat is tender.
Save broth for later.
Fry cauliflower and set aside.
Rinse rice in hot water & drain.
Add melted butter to rice.
Layer sliced tomatoes in a 6 qt. greased pan.
Next, layer the meat, then cauliflower, then the rice.
Pour the broth over the mixture & cover.
Boil for 5 mins.
Reduce the heat to simmer & cook for approx. 20 mins. or until rice is tender.
After cooking is completed, let the mixture cool for 10 mins.
Place a round dish to cover the top of the pan & turn over.
Garnish with pine nuts, browned in butter.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of pan; cover with cake mixture.
Combine confectioners sugar, margarine and cream cheese together.
Spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and drain the broccoli (do not cook).
In a mixing bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Add broccoli; fold in beaten eggs.
Place margarine and stuffing mix; sprinkle on casserole.
Bake at 350° in oven for about 45 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: mexican tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients except sour cream.
Take flour tortilla shells and spread about 2 tablespoons of sour cream onto shell. Then spread 1/4 cup cream cheese mixture on top of sour cream. Roll up and cut about 1-inch lengths.
Serve chilled with toothpicks and salsa.

title: vegetable broth
directions: In large saucepan place ingredients.
Cover with 3 quarts of water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to moderately low and simmer for 2 hours.
Strain before using.
Can be refrigerated for up to 3 days or frozen for up to 3 months.
Some sort of noodles can be added when serving.

title: marshmallow crispy treats
directions: Microwave butter for 45 seconds.
Add marshmallows; toss to coat with butter.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, when stirred.
Immediately add cereal; toss until coated.
Press into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: cream fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cream, water, corn syrup and salt; cook to soft ball stage (236°) or 240° above boiling point of water.
Remove from fire and allow to cool undisturbed until pan can be held with comfort.
Add flavoring; stir until creamy.
Add nuts and turn into buttered pan to harden.
Cut into squares.
May also be molded into various shapes.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: orange slice bars
directions: Combine half of the cake mix, water, eggs, butter and brown sugar.
Mix.
Blend in remaining cake mix.
Stir in orange slices. Spread in a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350 degree oven.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: quick corn chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: summer slush
directions: Blend with 6 cubes of ice in a blender.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix just enough to moisten.
Put into an oiled 8-inch baking pan.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: quick biscuits on grill
directions: Mix baking mix and water to form a soft dough; knead in 1/2 cup French fried onions into dough.
Roll out dough.
Cut into pieces and place on cookie sheet.
If desired, sprinkle the remaining French fried onions on top of pieces.

Place cookie sheet over a square pan of water and place on grill to cook (approximately 45 minutes, depending on how hot fire is) or put in oven (still using the pan of water) and cook at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll into balls.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes or until brown.

title: baked lasagna
directions: *Or use broad noodles and cottage cheese.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Cool overnight in refrigerator.
Peel eggs and cut in half.
Scoop out yolk into medium bowl.
Place white on nice tray.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Place in refrigerator.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix together and serve hot.
Keebler onion crackers are good with it.

title: banaha choctaw corn shuck bread
directions: Pour enough boiling water over the meal and soda mixture to make a soft dough which can be handled with the hands.

title: cranberry nut yellow salad
directions: Cook water, sugar and cranberries 10 minutes.
Microwave at High or cook 1 hour on stove.
Cool.
Mix pineapple, walnuts, apples and pecans.
Crush up the nuts.
Mix boiling water with the jello.
Add it to the mix and let it set.

title: baked mustard chicken
directions: Brush chicken with mustard and dredge in breadcrumbs.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: In bowl, mix with spoon the pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, pumpkin pie spices and salt.
Pour into 13 x 9 pan. Spread dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin mix.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped pecans over cake mix. Pour melted oleo over top and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to directions on box.
Drain. Add egg, soup and mayonnaise.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot sour cream potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes while still warm.
Add butter, pimento, onion and seasoning.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Stir in sour cream.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine pickles, onions, green peppers and salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain juice and place in large kettle.
Add sugar, turmeric, cloves, vinegar and water.
Boil 8 to 10 minutes or until pickles begin to turn clear.
Pack in hot jars and seal. Makes 7 pints.

title: apple fritter rings
directions: In a mixing bowl, thoroughly stir together flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, milk and cooking oil.
Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Place chicken and vegetables in baking dish.
Stir together soup, chicken broth and pepper.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Combine flour, milk and margarine.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix pasta, crab meat, shrimp and scallions. Blend chili sauce, mayonnaise, lemon juice and Old Bay seasoning with mixer. Reserve about 1/2 cup to 1 cup dressing and refrigerate. Pour remaining dressing over salad and mix thoroughly. Allow salad to refrigerate overnight. Add remaining dressing and mix thoroughly before serving.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients and store in a jar with a tight lid.
Use 1.5 teaspoons of mix for each cup of boiling water.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix buttermilk and soda; set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Cream sugar, oleo, Crisco and egg yolks; beat well.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk, beating well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites, pecans and coconut.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch pans at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend together cake mix, pie filling and eggs in a large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Spread half the batter in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; sprinkle with half the cinnamon-sugar.
Repeat with remaining batter and cinnamon-sugar.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool. Yield:
12 servings.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, dry ingredients, candy, oats
and
nuts.
Roll
into
small
balls and press on cookie sheet with floured fork.
Bake in 400° oven.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix
cream cheese, margarine, lemon juice, minced onion and mayonnaise with mixer.
Stir in celery and shrimp.
Serve as dip with crackers or as filling for small sandwiches.

title: mable v. brown's best-ever dark fruit cake
directions: In a heavy saucepan, cover raisins with water and cook until 1 cup of liquid remains.
Drain, reserving liquid, and allow to cool.

title: old mansion holiday cake
directions: Have shortening at room temperature and stir just to soften. Sift in dry ingredients.
Add 3/4 cup milk and mix until all flour is dampened.
Beat 2 minutes with mixer at low speed, or 300 strokes by hand.
Add two flavorings and mix.
Add meringue and the remaining milk and beat 150 strokes by hand or 1 minute by mixer at a low speed.
Turn batter into 2 round 9-inch layer cake pans that are 1 1/2 inches deep and have had the bottoms lined with waxed paper and have been greased.
Bake 30 minutes or until done. Cool.
Frost.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Put in greased baking dish.
Mix soup with milk.
Pour over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, green pepper, 1/2 cup picante sauce and cream cheese in a saucepan, over low heat, until smooth.
Spoon 1/3 cup of chicken mixture into each tortilla; roll up.
Place, seam side down, in lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: snowballs
directions: Form 6 scoops of ice-cream into smooth balls with ice-cream scooper. Roll each ball in 1/4 cup nuts; cover and refreeze.

title: sausage roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly flour surface and roll each loaf to an 11 x 8-inch rectangle.
Place sausage down the middle of loaf.
Layer 2 cups cheese and 1/2 of meat and spinach on both loaves.
Gently fold ends of bread over and pinch to seal.
Roll over onto 2 cookie sheets; pinched ends should be on bottom.
Brush egg white mixture over loaves.
Bake for 35 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 2 rolls.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter to a golden brown.
Combine in saucepan. Bring to boiling.

title: sassafras jelly
directions: Bring tea and honey to a slight boil.
Add pectin and root bark; simmer 6 minutes.
Put in hot jelly jars and cover.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cool complete saucepan.
When cool, add 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip.
Pour over five or more diced apples; mix well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: rosemary roasted potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch roasting pan.
Add potatoes, onions, carrots, olive oil, rosemary, salt and pepper; toss to coat all ingredients.
