Roast in oven, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until potatoes are pierced easily with a knife.
Makes 6 servings.

title: champagne dessert
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Keeps well in freezer.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix butter, sugar and flour together and press into a well buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 25 minutes. While this bakes, beat the eggs with fork and add lemon juice. Mix well and spoon over the baked crust.
Return to the oven and bake for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar while still hot.
Cut when cool.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all and refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into small balls and freeze on cookie sheets.
They can be stored
in plastic bags. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve as an appetizer.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In a separate bowl, mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
On a large platter (9 x 13-inch or 10-inch round), layer ingredients in the following order:
jalapeno dip, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, salsa, onions, tomatoes, olives and Monterey Jack cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Very good!

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine all ingredients, mixing well by hand.
Pour into pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
While cake is warm, pour prepared frosting over cake.

title: candied carrots(yields 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Peel and slice the carrots and cook them in boiling water until they are tender.
Drain off the water.
Add the unsalted butter and sugar to the carrots and cook until the butter and sugar are melted.

title: holiday balls
directions: Melt the margarine and the sugar in a saucepan. Chop the dates, add to the pan. Cook over a low heat until all of the ingredients blend and are like preserves. Remove from the heat and add the pecans, rice krispies and vanilla. Form the mixture into balls and roll in the powdered sugar. Delicious and pretty to serve.

title: shortbread
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla and mix until well blended. Gradually add flour until dough is not sticky to touch. Line bottom of jelly roll pan with wax paper and press dough flat to edges. Place another sheet of wax paper on top and roll surface until smooth with pastry roller. Refrigerate overnight. Cut into pieces (approximately 1 1/2 x 3-inches). Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: herbed spaghetti sauce
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic until meat is browned. Drain. Crush herbs.
Add rest of ingredients, including herbs. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: diet blueberry yogurt muffins
directions: Combine 1st 5 ingredients.
Make well in center.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Stir well.
Fold in blueberries.
Spray muffin pans with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins, 150 calories each.

title: wheat salad
directions: In mixing bowl, put cream cheese.
Sprinkle pudding over it and mix.
Add lemon juice and pineapple and mix.
Fold in wheat, nuts and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: marti's luscious (yet diet) dessert
directions: Butter the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Line with graham crackers (not crushed).
In a small bowl, mix vanilla pudding with 1 3/4 cups milk.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Blend in half of Cool Whip.
Spread over graham crackers in dish. Place a second layer of crackers.
Prepare chocolate pudding as above, folding in remaining Cool Whip.
Spread over second layer of crackers.
Chill 3 hours.
May be garnished with a dab of Cool Whip.

title: zesty snack mix(makes about 6 cups)
directions: In large bowl, combine popcorn and nuts; set aside.
In small bowl, combine margarine, mustard and salad dressing mix.
Pour over popcorn mixture, toss to coat well.
Spread in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir in raisins.
Spread on paper towels to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder, soda and salt.
Add shortening.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs; mix until smooth.
Add dry ingredients alternately with mashed bananas, stirring just enough to combine thoroughly.
Do not beat.
Turn into greased pan and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: plant food
directions: Mix ingredients in a gallon of tepid water.
Use only once a month.

title: pork and sauerkraut
directions: In Dutch oven, brown roast on all sides.
Add sauerkraut and juice, sugar and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 4 to 6 hours.

title: chili-cheesy rice
directions: Saute onion in	margarine
and	remove	from heat.
Add remaining ingredients, except
Cheddar cheese.
Spoon half the rice mixture into a
greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with half the cheese.
Repeat
with
remaining
rice mixture and cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: baked grapefruit
directions: Loosen sections of grapefruit; remove seed, if any.
Mix butter, sugar and cinnamon and pour evenly over grapefruit tops. Broil a few minutes until lightly browned.
Garnish with a whole strawberry in center of each grapefruit.
Serve as appetizer or dessert.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter or margarine together until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and cream until smooth.
Add egg and beat well.
Beat in peanut butter and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt together and add to creamed mixture.
Roll dough into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten by pressing with tip of teaspoon or fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans and lightly dust with flour or spray with nonstick spray.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes before turning out on board.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: crazy chicken casserole
directions: Pour drained vegetables into well-greased casserole dish. Cover with cubed chicken.
Pour half the soup over the mixture; season with salt and pepper.
Add rice and remaining soup.

title: empire state muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine apples and sugar.
Gently fold in cranberries, carrots and nuts.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to mixing bowl.
Mix well to moisten dry ingredients.
Combine eggs and oil.
Stir into apple mixture.
Fill muffin tins (greased) 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 18 to 24.

title: scripture cake
directions: Make it a family project to look up the ingredients.
All are found in the Bible (KJV).

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine oatmeal, sage, pepper, egg whites, onion, garlic and milk.
Add beef and mix lightly.
Place in a shallow baking pan (10-inches in diameter).
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Carefully drain fat from pan.

title: football chili
directions: Brown meat, chopped green pepper and onion.
Drain grease. Add kidney beans with juice.
Add hot salsa and can tomatoes. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and chili powder.

title: homemade mushroom spaghetti sauce
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, heat oil; saute onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water, mushrooms, oregano, basil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer gently, uncovered, for 30 minutes or longer, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot pasta.

title: main dish cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter 9-inch pie pan.
Blend milk, flour, salt and egg using an electric mixer.
Stir in half of cheese.
Pour into pie pan and bake until puffed and golden, about 25 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
Continue to bake until cheese has melted, about 4 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: chili-cheese dip(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat in microwave oven 5 to 6 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.
May reheat as needed.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix hamburger, rice and onion.
Shape into balls.
Brown in skillet, draining grease.
Mix tomato sauce, bell pepper and chili powder into same skillet.
Cook until done.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix and pour over steak to marinate for 6 to 8 hours in a glass cake pan.
Turn occasionally.
Broil 6 to 10 minutes on each side.
Cut in thin slices across the grain.

title: grandma's indian pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In top of double boiler, combine corn meal, 2 cups milk and salt.
Heat, stirring to prevent lumps, until slightly thickened, about 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: chinese beets
directions: Mix well, then cook for 3 minutes over medium heat or until the mixture thickens.
Let cool and refrigerate.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Place teriyaki sauce, sherry, sugar, garlic and ginger in shallow 2 1/2 quart microproof casserole; mix well.
Add steak and stir until coated.
Cover and marinate at room temperature 30 minutes; stirring occasionally.
Push meat to center of casserole. Arrange vegetables around steak.
Cover with casserole lid and cook on 80 for 10-13 minutes.
Serve with unseasoned rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hungarian meatballs
directions: Combine bread slices with all ingredients.
Shape in balls. Brown in oil; drain.
Simmer in spaghetti sauce for 1 hour.

title: izzie's potatoes
directions: Top with corn flakes (crushed) and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: celery seed bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine butter, celery seed, paprika and parsley flakes, stirring well to blend.
Spread on cut sides of each roll.
Place on baking sheet.
Broil until golden brown. Yields 4 servings.

title: homemade yogurt
directions: Combine gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Set aside to cool. Preheat oven to 275°.
Combine nonfat dry milk and 3 cups water. Add canned milk and sugar and gelatin mix.
Blend yogurt with remaining water and add to mixture.
Cover bowl with dish towel and put in oven.
Turn oven off.
Leave in oven 8 to 10 hours. If yogurt hasn't gelled, reheat oven and replace in oven for another 6 to 8 hours with oven off.
It will stiffen more when refrigerated.
May also be used in place of sour cream in recipes.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon strips to go on the top.
Mix all of the other ingredients together on top of the oven.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Add bacon about 15 minutes before done.

title: cherry salad delight
directions: Mix all and chill before serving.

title: friend helene's chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish.
Combine mayonnaise, onion soup mix, Russian dressing and preserves.
Pour mixture on chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Serve over rice.

title: pineapple orange punch
directions: Place sherbet in large punch bowl; add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Serves 50 people.

title: stuffing ala good
directions: Cook Uncle Ben's rice as package directs.
Stir-fry sausage and drain.
Cook mushrooms in butter and seasoning; don't drain.
Mix all together and keep warm in very low oven until cornish hens, chukkars, pheasant, doves, quail or chickens are ready.
A great favorite of hunters.
Even goes with venison with burgundy-olive oil and garlic sauce.

title: pineapple cheesecake squares
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Bake crust.
Beat cream cheese in medium bowl until smooth and fluffy; beat in 1/2 cup sugar and eggs.
Stir in 2/3 cup pineapple juice.
Pour cream cheese mixture over hot crust.
Bake just until center is set, about 20 minutes. Cool completely.
Mix flour and 1/4 cup sugar in 2 quart saucepan. Stir in 1 cup reserved pineapple juice.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; fold in pineapple.
Cool completely.
Beat whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Fold in pineapple mixture. Spread carefully over dessert.
Cover loosely and refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45-60 minutes.

title: barbecue pork chops or chicken
directions: Mix Coke and barbecue sauce together.
Place meat in casserole dish.
Cover with sauce and bake one hour at 350°.

title: fat man's misery
directions: Cover the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan with crumbled cookies. Cream together 1 cup 10x sugar with butter.
Add to this mixture the well beaten egg.
Blend.
Add almond flavoring.
Spread on top of cookies.
Beat or whip the cream until stiff.
Add sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Spread on top of butter mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours.
After eating your portion, roll until you've lost 5 pounds.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain
whole
kernel corn.
Melt margarine.
Beat eggs. Mix all ingredients (except cheese) in mixing bowl.
Pour in 2 quart casserole
dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 10 more minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix everything except cheese together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in water for 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and let cool.
Peel and cut 1/4-inch strips; set aside.
Combine 1/4 cup butter and next 5 ingredients in large bowl; gently stir in potatoes and cheese.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine 3 tablespoons butter and stuffing mix; sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: plecovnik(ham yeast bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast
in
warm
water and 1 tablespoon sugar. Combine water, potato,
1 tablespoon sugar, salt and oil.
Add to the yeast.
Stir
in
1/2 cups flour and beat well.
Let batter rise in
warm
place
until bubbly, about 40 to 50 minutes.
Then add
the
diced
ham.
Work
in flour one cup at a time.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Knead for about 5 minutes, place
in greased
bowl and grease top.
Let rise in warm place
until doubled in bulk.
Punch down, turn on flour board or surface. Then
shape
into
two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans that have
been greased.
Let
rise until double its bulk and bake in oven
for 40 minutes.
Depends on your oven. Brush top with warm water or melted butter.

title: mexican corn
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a heavy skillet.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in fried onions, tomatoes and oregano; cook, uncovered, 2 minutes or until tomatoes are thoroughly heated.

title: cabbage goulash
directions: Brown beef with bell pepper; drain and add cabbage, Ro-Tel and rice and cover with water.
Steam until cabbage is cooked to desired tenderness.

title: mindi's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil and water (mixture will be thick).
Add pumpkin, eggs and nuts.
Pour into 4 or 5 greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans (1/2 to 3/4 full) and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick rolls
directions: Combine half the flour and all of the yeast in a bowl and blend.
Add milk, water, sugar, salt and egg, then mix.
Beat with a beater about 3 minutes; add butter and remaining flour gradually and knead until smooth and satiny.
Place in a lightly greased bowl; grease surface of dough lightly.
Cover and allow to rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Turn out on lightly floured board; punch down and allow to rest about 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 36 parts and make into balls.

title: chicken and bow tie pasta(serves 4 to 5 hungry people)
directions: Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil.
Add pasta and beans. Cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently until just tender.

title: heather's cheese ball
directions: Set cream cheese out until soft, then add to bowl.
Put in all ingredients.
Stir until mixed up well.
Shape into ball and refrigerate.

title: zucchini relish
directions: You will need 6 small jars.

title: hot sausage bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Serve hot with warm cheese sauce.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package; drain.
Brown ground beef; drain off excess fat.
Combine ground beef, spaghetti sauce, tomato paste, green pepper, onion, salt, pepper, sugar and oregano in large bowl; stir well.
Spoon a little sauce in bottom of greased baking dish or pan.
Place a layer of noodles and a layer of sauce until all used.
Cover; bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove.
Put mushrooms and Mozzarella cheese on top; bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, uncovered.

title: six ingredient relish
directions: Chop onion, cucumbers, tomatoes and radishes in large bowl. Add drained corn and peas.	Pour Italian dressing over all ingredients.
Chill for about 1 hour.
Eat with meat and vegetables.
Keeps well for about a week, refrigerated.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Combine onion and water; let stand 10 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in onion and curry.
Saute 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Combine curry mixture with mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Blend.
Combine chicken, pineapple, nuts, raisins and apple in large bowl.
Add curry dressing and toss gently.
Line salad bowl with lettuce; add salad.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: creamed cauliflower casserole
directions: Break cauliflower into small pieces and cook until just tender.
Drain and place in a shallow 2-quart casserole.

title: mamaw's cranberry-nut bread
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder, soda and salt into bowl. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Combine orange juice and rind with egg.
Pour into flour mixture and mix just until flour is dampened.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Pour into floured and greased loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Cook noodles as directed on box.
Then put everything else into crock-pot and top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil and stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat or cake will be tough. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Put in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan (or 2 round 9-inch pans).
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes (30 to 35 for round pans).
Cool at least 15 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add buttermilk, eggs, coconut, dates, chopped walnuts, candy and soda.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Remove from oven.

title: chocolate chess
directions: Mix eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Melt oleo; add cocoa and sugar, mixing well.
Pour in 8-inch uncooked pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: annette's banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add egg and egg yolk and beat.
Add three medium very over ripe bananas.
(If your bananas are not very ripe, you will have to mash them; also,
the flavor will not be as good.)
Add vanilla.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk. Add chopped pecans.
Bake 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Check center with toothpick.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Poke holes in cake.
Mix the cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk together.
Pour over the cake.
Top with La Creme or Cool Whip and then the coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: amaretto tortoni
directions: In small bowl, beat egg whites.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff, glossy peaks.
In another bowl, beat heavy cream and Amaretto.
Fold egg whites into cream.
Spoon into 3 ounce paper cups; cover with almonds and freeze.

title: etouffee
directions: Saute vegetables in butter; add seafood and cook a few minutes.
Add soup and broth; simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: summer lime chicken breasts
directions: Trim fat.
Pound between waxed paper to flatten slightly. Combine ingredients and pour over chicken.
Marinate for 1 hour. Grill or broil 5 minutes on each side.

title: chocolate mounds
directions: Mix sugar, coconut, pecans and salt together.
Melt butter (don't get too hot).
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix ingredients together and then form into balls.
Chill 12 to 14 hours. Mix chips and paraffin in double boiler. Stir until melted.
Dip chilled mounds in chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: chocolate buttermilk bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan.
Combine sugar and butter.
Blend thoroughly.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in buttermilk.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir just until dry particles are moist.
Stir in nuts. Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool.

title: frozen chocolate mousse pie
directions: *Or make your own crust using 2 cups finely crushed cream-filled chocolate cookies (about 20 cookies) and 1/4 cup margarine or butter melted.
Combine cookie crumbs and margarine; press on bottom and up sides to rim of a lightly buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.
(The graham cracker pie crust works great.)

title: butter pecan pie squares
directions: Combine in a medium bowl the flour and sugar; cut in the butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Press mixture evenly into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: potatoes gourmet
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Cool, peel and grate coarsely. Combine 1/4 cup butter and cheese, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Spoon mix into 2-quart shallow casserole; dot with butter.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
James could live on potatoes!

title: carrots with orange and cardamon(yields 4 servings)
directions: Thinly slice carrots.
Squeeze orange, reserving both juice and pulp.
Saute carrots with cardamon in hot butter for about 15 minutes.
Add orange juice and pulp.
Season with pepper and cook until tender.
Enjoy!

title: micro - caramel corn
directions: Melt and stir first 3 ingredients together in a tall bowl. Boil for 2 minutes.
Add soda.
Put popped popcorn in a brown grocery bag, pour mix over, close bag, shake and microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake; microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake; microwave 1 minute.
Spread on tray to cool.

title: shortcakes
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° until done, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chinese beets
directions: I use 2 cans of beets.

title: lasagne
directions: Beat egg with Ricotta cheese.
Fry hamburger.
Add sauce, then layer (cover).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: breakfast before casserole
directions: Saute sausage and drain.
Place cubed bread on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with sausage and cheese. Pour eggs beaten with milk, salt and mustard.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap and refrigerate.
Put in cold oven and set at 350° or 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion in frypan. Drain beans and add to ground beef mixture.
Add tomato soup to mixture and stir.
Place in casserole dish and put potatoes on top. Put in 350° oven until potatoes are a little crisp (about 15 or 20 minutes).

title: chilled strawberry soup
directions: In a 1-quart stainless steel saucepan, bring wine and ginger to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add heavy cream; return to boiling and cook 1 minute longer, stirring constantly. Remove pan from heat.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done; mash.
Beat in cream cheese, 1 stick margarine, sour cream, garlic salt and pepper.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Delicious.

title: baked french toast
directions: Melt margarine, brown sugar and corn syrup and pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Arrange slices of bread in pan.
Beat 3 eggs, 3/4 cup milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla together.
Pour over bread. Refrigerate overnight and bake in the morning at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water; cool.
Beat butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Beat into chocolate mixture alternately with buttermilk. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer pans, lined on bottoms with waxed paper. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes
or until cake springs back when pressed in center.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pans and finish cooling.
Spread Coconut-Pecan Frosting between layers and over top of cake.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well. Spoon into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: carrot pudding cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and rind and beat until smooth.
Spread creamy orange frosting between layers and on top of cake and sides.
Garnish with pecans.

title: kay lynn's mexican layered casserole
directions: In a medium-size bowl, mix soup, Ro-Tel water, onion and the cubed Velveeta.
Mix well.
In a baking dish, place your first layer of tortillas, then a layer of the beef.
Then a layer of the mix.
Repeat until you've used up the ingredients.
Bake in a medium oven for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix sweet potatoes with all other ingredients, except marshmallows, with electric mixer.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Mix yellow cake mix as directed on package and pour into oblong baking dish.
Cook as directed.
Cool 2 hours.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating until thick and foamy.
Stir in pineapple and zucchini.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Spread on rack to cool completely.

title: night before casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in a greased 10 x 15-inch casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover the next day.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apple pie(2 crust)
directions: Line 9 or 10-inch pie pan with crust. Add apples and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add sugar, butter, spice, salt and cornstarch. Put top crust on and seal edges. Slash top crust. Bake in 425° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Crust should be brown.

title: florence wassman's sponge cake
directions: Whip egg yolks and mix all ingredients together.
Whip and fold in egg whites.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with 6 sliced apples. Refrigerate any unused portions.

title: dreamsicle salad
directions: Put Cool Whip and orange Jell-O in a large bowl.
Mix together well. Add cottage cheese and oranges and mix together real good. Chill until ready to serve.

title: vegetable stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash squash thoroughly.
Place in a saucepan with water to cover and bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 8 minutes until tender but firm.
Drain and cool to touch.
Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Remove and reserve pulp, leaving shell firm. Chop pulp.
Combine pulp and next 5 ingredients.
Place shells in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon vegetable mixture into shells. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes. Transfer to serving platter.
Yields 8 servings.
Contains 34 calories per serving.

title: ambrosia mold salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to make 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Add pineapple juice with water.
Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened (consistency of egg whites).
Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Stir in pineapple, oranges and marshmallows.
Spoon into 6-cup mold or 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.

title: christmas nut rolls
directions: Beat eggs.
Add vanilla, yeast and milk.
Mix all liquids and shortening with fingers.
Mix dry ingredients with 3 cups of flour.
Mix with liquids until dough no longer sticks to fingers. (You may need to add more flour.) Refrigerate dough 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Put damp cloth on top of bowl while refrigerating. Roll out individual cookies and fill with nuts or apricots.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to sugar/egg mixture.
Add oatmeal.
Stir batter only enough to make it smooth.
Add raisins and nuts.
On greased pan, drop dough by teaspoonful.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine yeast, sugar and warm water.
Add egg, salt and shortening.
Stir in all of flour and blend well.
Let stand in bowl 30 minutes before making into rolls.
Drop in 9 x 13-inch pan with tablespoon.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: chicken breasts in phyllo
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Over medium heat, melt butter (2 tablespoons) in skillet; add mushrooms and tomatoes.
Let mixture cook dry (about 4 minutes).
Turn off; pour mixture into mixing bowl.
Add thyme and cheese; mix and add pinch of salt and pepper and mix again.
Open chicken breast; sprinkle with pinch of salt and pepper.
Stuff with cheese mixture.
Fold breast around itself.
Lay 1 sheet of phyllo dough on clean surface; brush sheet with melted butter and place another
sheet over the buttered sheet and brush with melted butter.
Cut phyllo in half, making 2 squares.
Place one square on top of other,
making total of 4 layers of dough.
Place chicken breast in middle of phyllo square. Fold around breast, sealing breast inside dough.
Place on baking sheet, seam side down.
Repeat process for other 3 breasts.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, depending on size of breasts.
Serve immediately while dough is crispy.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles, mix tuna, cream of celery soup, cheese and peas. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Add noodles.
Put in a 9 X 13 baking pan.
Crumble crackers on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes.

title: lobster bisque
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Stir and simmer.
Add lobster pieces.
Simmer to desired temperature.
Do not boil.

title: apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place apples, sugar and dry cake mix in layers in a greased 9 or 10-inch square baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over top of cake mix.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Continue baking for 15 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream, if wanted.

title: bryce's strawberry pie
directions: Mix
sugar
and cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water and dash of salt.
Mix all with 1 cup water and cook until thick. Add
food coloring and lemon juice.	Cool and mix with 1 pint strawberries. Pour into pie shell.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and roll in either nuts or bacon bits.

title: eggy corn patch casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Serve piping hot.
Good with green salad.
Serves 8.

title: beef noodles casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain and mix with remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: In a buttered casserole dish, arrange a layer of potatoes, half of the ground beef, all the onion and remainder of beef. Spread the soup over top of casserole.
Arrange remainder of potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candy apple pie
directions: Line a 9-inch deep dish pie pan with crust.
Peel and slice apples; fill crust with apples and red hots (fill to heaping). Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix oleo, sugar and flour until crumbly.
Mix in crushed nuts.
Spread on top of apples and red hots.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until browned and bubbly.

title: no fail peach pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2 1/2-quart Pyrex dish.
Place in oven and bake at 325° until crust comes to top and browns.

title: hawaiian nut bread
directions: Using a large mixing bowl, combine the dry ingredients.
Drain the pineapple.
Add all of the remaining ingredients to the dry mixture and stir until well blended.
Pour the batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix all
ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at
for	15
to	20 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool completely.

title: cucumber cream cheese spread or cucumber roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients together.
(Could set overnight if you wished.)
Spread on crackers.

title: hamburger-vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add meat and cook until all the pink has disappeared.
Add celery, carrots, green pepper, beef bouillon cube, hot water and seasonings.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Mix flour and cold water until smooth and add to mixture.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Spoon fluffy mashed potatoes around edge of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until the top has become a golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: tangy baked chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
Combine the red and black peppers; rub over chicken breasts.
Combine the salad dressing, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Lightly brush both sides of chicken breasts with some of the dressing mixture.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In skillet, cook sausage until browned; drain.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles and place on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points aimed toward center, press over bottom and up sides to form crust.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour and baking powder (mixed together).
Dissolve Sugar Twin in combined vanilla and milk.
Stir into flour mixture.
Sprinkle in cinnamon and knead so it swirls in.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Smash with fork that has been dipped in water.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Measure 1 1/2 cups juice and water into microwave-safe bowl. Stir in pudding mix.
Microwave 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Cool.
Add drained fruit.
Refrigerate.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off grease.
Cook lasagne. In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer lasagne, beef, then cheese.
Make 2 to 3 layers; save enough cheese to cover top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: grandma's chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, salt, vanilla and eggs until creamy. Mix flour and cocoa together, then add to sugar mixture, a little at a time, and a little buttermilk at the time, until all is mixed well.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: In a skillet, saute onion and green pepper in margarine to wilt; add salt and chili powder.
Mix together soups and tomatoes; add sauteed onion and pepper mixture.
Quickly dip tortillas in boiling chicken broth to wilt; cut in strips.
Layer half of tortilla strips in a greased 2-quart oblong casserole.
Layer half of chicken over tortillas; add half of soup mixture and half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: royal rhubarb crisp(serves 8)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in 8-inch square ungreased casserole.
Toss lightly to mix.
Let stand 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine last 6 ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until rhubarb is tender.

title: oatmeal raisin bread
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl. Add 2 cups boiling water. Stir to melt oleo and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve the yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water and add to above mixture. Gradually stir in the flour, enough to make a soft dough.
Knead 5 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise until double in size.
Punch down.
Let rest 10 minutes. Cut dough into 2 or 3 mounds.
Roll each portion to a rectangle.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon and spread on dough.
Roll up, starting at short end. Fit into greased loaf pans.
Let raise again. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes. Brush with oleo while warm.
I bake in 3 loaf pans for a shorter time.

title: good stuff
directions: Mix and spread on a cookie sheet covered with wax paper. Freeze 1/2 hour.
Break into small pieces.

title: blueberry wheat muffins
directions: Mix together all ingredients except blueberries in a medium mixing bowl.
Add and fold in blueberries.
Pour into muffin tins which have been sprayed with non-stick cooking spray.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time (beat well after each addition).
Sift dry ingredients; add mixture.
Add nuts, pineapple and carrots last.
Bake in 3 layer pans at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick and easy supper
directions: Form meat into individual loaf size.
Place on a piece of aluminum foil.
Over meat, place potatoes, onions and carrots. Sprinkle salt over vegetables.
Wrap securely and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: salmon noodles romanoff
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook noodles; drain.
Mix noodles, cottage cheese, sur cream, onion, garlic, Worcestershire, red pepper sauce, salt and salmon.
Place about 1 cup salmon mixture in each of 5 or 6 greased baking shells or individual casseroles. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: turkey pot pie(4 servings)
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add vegetables and saute 5 minutes.
Add condensed soup, spices and turkey to vegetable mixture.
Pour into pie shell and cover with top crust.
Press together edges.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 40 minutes.

title: cocktail meats
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; put in crock-pot.
Add one kind of meat for each crock-pot of sauce.
Cook on low for 2 to 3 hours.

title: ritz bits snacks
directions: Whisk oil, cheese and dressing.
Toss crackers in oil.
Bake on cookie sheet at 200° for 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes and combine in large mixing bowl with 1/2 cup melted butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; blend together.
Place in greased 3-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; melt butter.
Combine ingredients, except pecans. Mix well and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.	Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until firm in center.

title: cheese cookies(country:  u.s.a.)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until smooth and then stir in Rice Krispies.
Make small balls and flatten.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread each ingredient evenly in order given.
Put margarine into thin slices and spread over top.
Place in middle rack of oven and bake for one hour at 350° or until firm in center.
Cool before serving. Serves at least 12.

title: turtle dessert
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Pour on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Stir often so it browns evenly.
Cool. Put half in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Drizzle chocolate topping over mixture. Slice ice cream and place over chocolate topping. Drizzle caramel topping over ice cream.
Top with remaining crumbs. Freeze overnight.

title: tami's casserole
directions: Combine everything, except 1/2 the cheese, onions and rolls. Put in pan.
Bake, covered, at 375°.
Separate rolls.
Make rectangles (cut lengthwise) into 3 strips.
Put on casserole to make lattice top.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake for 20 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: rolled dumplings
directions: Cook roasting chicken, baked or boiled.
If baked, will need to add enough water to juice from chicken to make 4 quarts of liquid.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in only until blended 2/3 cup milk.
Roll out on floured paper or board. Cut in 2-inch squares.
Drop individually into boiling liquid.
Do not cover.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar, combine eggs and sour cream; add to mixture.
Stir flour, salt and soda together; add to mixture.
Spread 1/2 of dough in 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread pie filling over top of dough.
Sprinkle 1/2 of sugar/cinnamon mixture over filling.
Spread remaining dough on top and sprinkle with rest of sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Delicious.

title: klooz crispy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking dish with butter.
In a freezer bag, finely crush Ritz crackers, then mix rest of ingredients.
Drop chicken, one piece at a time, into freezer bag. Shake until well coated and place in baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes. Turn and add 2 tablespoons of melted butter and remaining cracker mixture.
Return to oven and bake until done (approximately 20 minutes more).

title: ham and egg pie
directions: Layer ham, then eggs and sprinkle cheese all over top.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: surprise cake
directions: Mix all wet ingredients together.
Add and beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and raisins (optional).
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tom's tuna salad
directions: Put chopped
lettuce
in
a bowl.
Add tuna and Miracle Whip; mix.
Add
peas,
tomatoes,
several dashes of hot sauce and a little pepper.
Mix again.
Adjust seasoning.
Now, you can either put some dry noodles in a bowl and put salad on top or mix in the dry noodles and serve chilled.
Remember the dry noodles will get soggy,
so
don't add until you are ready to serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into an uncooked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes in 300° oven.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Pour macaroni into melted butter and stir until coated.
Sprinkle grated cheese through macaroni.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mom's chocolate cheese
directions: Optional:
Nuts and marshmallows for topping and honey for sugar.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, water and milk.
Chill 5 minutes.
Mix in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer in large bowl with bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: homemade chocolate pudding and pie mix
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well. Store in an airtight container.
Stir mix before each use.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ketchup, together in 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Spread ketchup over top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce pan cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and applesauce.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to the first mixture, alternating with water.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: frosted chocolate brownie supreme
directions: 1. Beat margarine at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy; gradually add sugar and beat well. Add
eggs whites, sour cream, milk, and vanilla. Beat well.
2. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients. Stir well. Add
flour mixture to creamed mixture, mixing well.
3. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan coated with cooking
spray. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a wooden
toothpick comes out clean.
4. Cool in pan or a wire rack. Spread creamy chocolate
frosting over cooled brownies and cut into squares.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, using only 2 cups of milk; beat for 1 minute. Fold in whipped topping.
Line bottom of 12 x 9-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Spread 1/2 of pudding mixture on top. Layer again with graham crackers and the rest of pudding.
Top layer with graham crackers again and spread chocolate frosting over them.
Chill for 12 to 14 hours before serving.

title: fudge
directions: Stir together; bring slowly to a boil.
Watch carefully as it sticks.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour over 1st mixture and stir until thoroughly blended.
Pour in buttered pans.
Makes 3 (9 x 9-inch) pans.
Will freeze.

title: bambinos
directions: Mix tomato paste, garlic salt and oregano in bowl with fork. Arrange crackers on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread about 1 teaspoon tomato paste mixture on each cracker with spatula.
Top each cracker with 1 pepperoni slice.
Sprinkle the pepperoni with shredded cheese.
Place in oven at 350° until melted.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Heat tuna and cream of chicken together.
Boil noodles until done; drain.
Mix together.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: unbelievable appetizer
directions: Combine cocktail sauce with grape jelly in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until jelly is dissolved.
Add wieners or meatballs. Serve hot in chafing dish or warming tray with toothpicks.

title: pizza dough
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water in a small bowl.
Stir to dissolve. Let stand about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and salt to make a soft dough.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes, adding more flour, if needed.
Shape into a ball and place in a greased bowl; turn to coat.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 425°. Sprinkle two round 12-inch pizza pans with cornmeal.
Punch down dough and divide in half.
Roll or pat into two 12-inch circles. Top as desired.
Bake 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: peanut butter drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat well.
Mix in sifted flour, soda and salt.
Shape into small balls and flatten.
Bake on cookie sheet 10 minutes in moderate oven (375°).
Makes 44 small cookies.
